name: Buckeye Food Stop
address: 1282 Essex Ave, Columbus, OH 43201, USA

reviews.text:
OMG! I stopped here as my daughter recommended. Her and her entire Lacrosse team stopped here on Friday night after their games. She shared that their was a ROBOT delivering food and how good her food was. She is picky so I had to stop by before I left town.

Lots of traffic but they were in and out. Talked with a customer and he gave a great recommendation and showed me his ate of food.

I ordered Soul food. Catfish, pork chops, cabbage, greens, macn' cheese, spaghetti, fried okra mash potatoes, and peach cobbler. And some crab rangoons ( different restaurant).

My husband was thrilled and so was my sister as I shared when I got back to KY.

I wish I could share pics but they ate too fast.

Yep, 5+ stars.

And I saw the robot!!

Given an order time and waited 30 mins after before the food was “being prepared” .. I ordered a 10 piece fried meal, 3 sides, a jerk chicken meal… $90… and only got the fried chicken meal and three sides.. I don’t live close enough to turn around and go back.. but I searched the restaurant “From The Soul” and there is ABSOLUTELY no way to contact them.. a $90 bucket of 10 pieces of fried chicken.. yea not buying that again 🙅🏽‍♂️🫡

There is no atmosphere as this is a ghost kitchen with only small area to sit down but that’s okay.  Food was ready quite fast.  I ordered from Maria’s quesadillas.  The portion size is large for the price you pay so I feel like you get a good value.  Easy enough to share a 12” quesadilla for two.  The quesadilla was good.  It was anything unique and tasted fine.  It had some cheese that must fall out during cooking and gets cooked to quesadilla.  Overall was just good

Soul 2 Go inside Buckeye Food Stop!This is the 4th time we have chosen this place, Catfish is amazing (from a Southern boy) and tried the wings today, excellent! All side dishes have been super flavorful.

Food tasted good . Didn’t come with utensils and it was bowl with three different items I needed it for . Service was fast and got food sooner than I thought . Food is priced 4 out of 5. Could be a couple dollars cheaper and I would visit more often honestly .

profile: Buckeye Food Stop is a Restaurant restaurant in columbus with a Unknown price range. It has a rating of 4.6/5. It is known for being affordable and quick service. Popular dishes include Soul, Catfish and Fried Chicken.

name: Northstar Cafe in the Short North
address: 951 N High St, Columbus, OH 43201, USA

reviews.text: Went for breakfast on Sunday morning.  The line was short, and we ordered our food. It was a little crowded but we found a seat inside. We got biscuits and gravy and the mushroom frittata with orange juice and a coffee. The food was good. The food is brought to your table after you order at the counter. There is searing outside. Parking is located behind the restaurant.  There is a lot that is shared with other retailers. There is a ramp for wheelchairs from the sidewalk to the entrance.

This place was amazing.  Staying in Columbus for the weekend and stopped in for Sunday brunch.   The food was absolutely delicious.  The sweet potato fries with the dipping aoli was bliss.  Had hot coffee to get worked up and a drink menu to start the week right.
Amazing lunch spot, place for coffee, or to grab a drink. Great wood decor. I had the chicken avocado sandwhich and it was better lunches I can remember. I’ll probably come back here during my trip.
Most amazing lunch ever!! Gluten free bun is phenomenal! Best sweet potato fries! Made to order guacamole is out of this world!  Wish there was one of these in Colorado!

Delicious. I actually love meat but I recently decided I need to start eating more vegan options. This Thai burrito did not disappoint. The only thing that didn’t mesh with the burrito was the parsley. It too bright in and grey painting. I would ask to remove in the future. I chose tofu as my protein. I typically still feel hungry after eating all veggies but , I'm full.  Very good. I also got the carrot cake. Yummy

profile: Northstar Cafe in the Short North is a Restaurant, Café restaurant in columbus with a $$ price range. It has a rating of 4.5/5. It is known for being quick service and healthy. Popular dishes include There and Sunday.

name: Budd Dairy Food Hall
address: 1086 N 4th St, Columbus, OH 43201, USA

reviews.text: This sounds like a foodie paradise! The lack of mall distractions and the pure focus on the culinary experience is truly something to aspire for. The taco restaurant and southern restaurant pairing is already mouth-watering and with the unique flavors of Filipino street food and Pokebap, it's a feast for the taste buds. The clean, unique ambience with friendly service adds to the whole experience. The rooftop bar and patio are the icing on the cake, allowing one to enjoy the view and relax while enjoying the food. Places like this are truly worth visiting again and again! What's your favorite restaurant?

Always great service.
Parking can be difficult but usually not bad.
Neat concept with three floors, bars on each floor.
Rooftop bar is fun, library is neat, food hall has so many options.
Try a drink of the month.
Ask for Frank .

What a cool food hall! Everyone was extremely friendly upon entry from the hostess when you first enter to all businesses we encountered. The modern decor was very pleasing to the eyes. This is a great place to have a drink and watch a game with plenty of options for everyone to select and it was open late on Sundays.

AWESOME!  What a neat spot. Eight or nine vendors offering a huge variety of food. I have to admit, I saw LOTS of people with rice bowls but my wife and I both ordered from Cluck Norris. Delish! It's designed to be easy. Browse past the kitchens themselves, or grab your seat at the bar and check out the food using QR codes, order, pay, get a text, and enjoy.
We didn't even get to check out the second floor!
Travelers' Tip: If you see a parking spot on the street just take it. No reason to wiggle through their tight parking lot, especially close to lunch or supper time.
Pic is, like, 1/4 of the main space.

I’m not sure where to leave my review. I enjoyed the Jerk Spot in the Hatch Pop Up Kitchen. So I guess it’s not a permanent vendor. I was having a hard time deciding what to get for my birthday dinner. The staff talked me into the oxtail, and they did not steer me wrong. Steer me. I just now enjoyed my own punny. The only thing that I can think of to make that experience better would have been to not eat out of styrofoam. We dined in. I could have used a plate. I do look forward to returning and seeing who is in the pop up kitchen. But I already have plans for some tacos and the catfish!

name: Varsity Club Restaurant & Bar
address: 278 W Lane Ave, Columbus, OH 43201, USA

reviews.text:
So the good, cheap drinks, bar nuts, and cool atmosphere and alumni that you can talk to.

The bad: went in on a Sunday afternoon, like 6 people at the bar. The two girls bartending were more concerned with their friends at the end and made us wait 20 minutes for the first drink. The guys next to us literally had to yell to stop the sorority fest to be able to pay for their food. Probably a great place, but the kids working the bar were helpless.
A pretty good place to watch a game and enjoy a drink and some food.
Drove down from Pontiac, Michigan to have lunch. This place didn't disappoint
Have no expectations when visiting. Nice establishment.  Regular tasting bar food. The bathrooms are horribly small. Customer service was above par. Decent number of tvs to watch a game.

Was here Saturday for a good part of the game, our waitress Quinn was top tier. She was amazing considering how busy it was! She kept our drinks full, food coming and always checked on us. Had such a blast here and will be coming back for sure!

profile: Varsity Club Restaurant & Bar is a Restaurant, Bar/Pub restaurant in columbus with a $ price range. It has a rating of 4.3/5. It is known for being affordable and family friendly.

name: Bakersfield Short North
address: 733 N High St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

reviews.text: Quite possibly the best fish tacos here in Cols.  I have been coming here since they opened over 10 years ago now, and their fish taco has remained consistent.  Crispy fried mahi-mahi with tabasco lime sauce, citrus slaw, cilantro and a wedge of lime.  Highly recommended!

My biggest gripe about Columbus is that the Mexican food sucks. And Bakersfield was probably the best I’ve had (or after so long my standards have lowered), but the chips here were good and I forgot to take pictures of my tacos but they were well prepared.

Not authentic and you pay for chips but a variety of high top tables on high street, I would return.

Randomly decided to go to a bookstore then get tacos on a Saturday night. I miss read the menu and picked this place thinking they had horchata. They do, but as a cocktail. It was delicious anyway.

The food was so so good. The best thing ended up being the elote salad. The corn tasted like freshly cut off the cob corn. 5stars for that alone.

My only very minor complaint, I wish they had desserts, even if it was only  mango and chamoy.

Spectacular experience. We had a somewhat odd situation where we asked for a last minute catering order and they were able to accommodate. Great communication and staff service, and of course, excellent food.

We had to move away from Columbus a couple years ago and we still come here wherever we're back in town. Love it.

Sat at the bar and the bartender was attentive and thoughtful. This was my first time in Columbus and it was a welcoming feeling. The food was absolutely delicious! Try the tacos and you obviously won't be disappointed!

name: Saturn's Sports Bar Columbus, Ohio
address: 1288 N High St, Columbus, OH 43201, USA

reviews.text: When a sports bar says they have the best wings in Ohio I often don't believe them..... but these wings are literally out of this world (pun INTENDED). We slid in here to watch the wild card game and it was awesome!! Also the chips and salsa??? Amazing they had a homemade feel! Definitely stopping back in next time I'm here!

TLDR: GET THE WINGS
This place is truly a sports bar, TVs all over with something playing for everyone. We were a little nervous when we arrived, we were the only customers at 7pm on a Saturday. But service was quick and attentive from behind the bar staff. We got the house chips and salsa, absolutely delicious. I got the chicken tacos and my fiancé got the wings, half buffalo half BBQ. I am not a bone in wing person by any means but these things were INCREDIBLE. My fiancé says the buffalo wings were delicious and but I tried a BBQ wing and let me tell you… those were insane. Like we got more to take home and make friends try because they were SO GOOD. The drinks were delicious and well-poured. On our way out we notice a back room area and private karaoke room?? We will be coming back to explore the rest of this place for sure!

Bartender was extremely personable and kind. Owner was there and gave me a tour of the new gaming and social spaces they've added. This location on campus has a few accessible features to it, but while visiting the inside, I noticed some areas that could be upgraded to make it even more accessible. A few things I had noticed upon entering is there are two separate entrances, one with a handicap button and one without, and either way you enter, the doors are made of wood and seem to be fairly heavy for someone in a wheelchair. With the entrance that has the handicap button on the outside, the button seems to be a decent size to press for someone, but the door tends to only stay open for 3-5 seconds. This seems to be a short timeframe, in my opinion, as it may take longer for frequent users of the handicap button to get through the doors. I did not see a handicap button inside the doors, while leaving the establishment.
There are no ramps or stairs which does make the area a bit more accessible, and along with this there is a variety of seating inside (booths, tables, comfortable chairs, etc.) and at all different heights as well. This makes things a bit easier for anyone with a disability and gives a wide selection of choices for all people who eat there. However, I noticed there are lots of tables in the side rooms that are within 3 feet or less of each other, and with chairs not pushed in, this creates barriers for any wheelchair users or blind individuals.
I will say, most of the countertops are at a great height for reaching and grabbing everything you may need (cups, ordering off the iPad at the front, and sauces), but if you are placing a to-go order, the shelves that the food is placed on for those orders tend to become too high to reach for your food whenever it is ready. Also, they do have screens located up above behind the counter that shows when your food is being prepared and when it is ready which is helpful for any deaf or HOH individuals to follow along with when needed.
Overall, this location does a good job at keeping some factors in mind for individuals with a disability, but there could always be upgrades and changes to make the establishment even more comfortable for those individuals!

reviews.text:
Bristol Republic, Columbus, OH - An Authentic Nashville Experience in the Heart of Short North

Imagine stepping into a space that feels like a slice of Nashville right in the heart of Columbus, Ohio. That’s exactly what you get at Bristol Republic, located at 1124 N High St, Columbus, OH. Known for its lively atmosphere, Bristol Republic offers a unique blend of in-house smoked BBQ, a vast selection of rare bourbons and whiskeys, and a vibrant music scene.

As soon as you enter, the rustic charm of exposed brick and soft lighting invites you into a warm, welcoming space. The bar showcases over 150 rare bourbon and whiskey selections, ranging from well-known distilleries to unique, independent labels. It’s a whiskey lover’s paradise, providing the perfect backdrop for an evening of relaxation or celebration.

The food at Bristol Republic is nothing short of impressive. The menu features competition-quality BBQ, smoked daily, ensuring that each dish is rich with flavor and perfectly tender. From brisket to ribs, every item promises to satisfy your BBQ cravings, paired beautifully with their hand-crafted sides.

But Bristol Republic isn’t just about great food and drinks. It’s a hub for live music, with performances from Thursday through Sunday, bringing the spirit of Nashville’s music scene to Columbus. Whether you’re there for a quiet dinner or a lively brunch, the live music adds an extra layer of enjoyment to your visit.

One of the most talked-about features is the unique restroom setup, with creatively designed elements that add a quirky touch to the venue. It’s part of the charm that makes Bristol Republic not just a place to eat and drink, but a full experience.

For those looking to explore a little taste of Nashville in Columbus, Bristol Republic is a must-visit. Remember to follow @realriguin on Instagram for more delicious food reviews and snapshots of my culinary adventures!

Location and Hours:
•	Address: 1124 N High St, Columbus, OH 43201
•	Hours: Thursday 4pm-12am, Friday-Saturday 10am-2:30am, Sunday 10am-10pm

So next time you’re in the Short North area, don’t miss out on this Nashville-inspired gem. Whether it’s the food, the drinks, or the music, Bristol Republic promises an unforgettable experience.
Popped in for a quick brunch on the way home from Cincy. Great plates and beer, at an excellent price. Our bartender was super attentive and positive. We'll definitely be back.

They boast that it is good and it really is! The fried pickles are crisp and plentiful. They start you out with 2 dipping sauces- well done!!

The chicken tenders were so delicious- scratch made, succulent and scrumptious! Juicy and crispy. The right amount of waffle fries.

We had a combo meat platter to split between the 2 of us and still took some home. All was excellent. The collards side is a must have and ample to share!

The place was lively and hopping. We enjoyed a table dining experience around 5ish on Saturday and they were getting busy when we left.

The Bloody Mary was also very delicious.
We also enjoyed the carafe of water left in the table.

The decor is cute but not overly done and the country music is the best of what Nashville has to offer, with some great throwbacks!

I came here for Sunday brunch one time. The place has a very solid, BBQ-focused menu, and even the breakfast dishes have some BBQ flare to them.. lots of dishes that would put you to sleep! It has a chill bar vibe, with lots of TVs, and a decent-sized patio for a nice day. We ordered a ton of starters, and I thought they were the star of the show. The brisket on top of the tots and nachos was excellent. I never imagined BBQ sauce and nachos could make such a good combo. Both dishes were overloaded with good stuff!.. I don't know how else to put it. The hush puppies were excellent, too. The cinnamon roll was a 6/10 for me; twas a little crunchier than I'd like. All the main dishes on our table looked amazing, and generally, everybody was happy. I had the brisket and eggs, which wasn't as flavourful and exciting as the starters, but still a solid meal. Service was pretty good and quick, despite a bigger party. I'd be happy to come back.

I feel like i’ve been transported to the 70s. Service is always great and ive never had a bad time here. There are two floors and an outdoor area. Perfect Perfect Perfect.

I had a great time at Good Night John Boy in Columbus! The atmosphere was super fun with awesome 70s vibes, great music, and a lively crowd. The service was friendly and efficient. It’s the perfect spot for a fun night out with friends. Definitely looking forward to going

Had my date party there last might and it was THE BEST! drinks were amazing and the vibe was just immaculate. I would go there everyday if i could. The place has such a great vibe and the managers were very polite.  GO THERE!!!!

Security thought it was a good idea to throw my buddy across the bar for no good reason. He's a very calm and collected dude, and I've heard there has been problems with this guard in the past. reviews.text: Came here to get the Peking Duck dinner for Father’s Day since I heard they have the best in Columbus. It was well-worth the money and left us with plenty of leftovers! It was the full authentic four-course meal, with my favorite being the soup. Everything was absolutely delicious and the woman serving us was so sweet and helpful with the menu. She made us feel right at home, even though it was our first time there. I’m absolutely coming back to try more.

The sweet lady that owns this place made the whole visit. She was kind and excited for a new customer. This restaurant has been here for over 30 years.

The egg roll is handmade. Probably the best egg roll I’ve had in my life.

Portions are enough for two meals.

The roast duck is the best.
The rice noodle is the worst.
Fried rice is not so good.
This place is delicious, everyone there is super kind, and the food is reasonably priced. The tea is great too. Definitely my favorite place to eat near OSU’s campus. 10/10 would recommend

The woman that answered to take my order was so pleasant. When I got there she still had the same nice dameanor. After using the checkout tablet she offered me hand sanitizer, which usually never happens when I go to a restaurant, even with covid and everything literally the first restaurant to offer that. The Sesame sauce is more like there own kind of BBQ sauce as they stated in the menu. Overall a very good experience and the best part was the EGG ROLL !!!!! I ONLY GOT ONE AND PROBABLY SHOULD HAVE GOTTEN 3 PORK EGG ROLLS !!! ID GO HERE FOR THE EGG ROLLS ALONE. Highly recommend, very fresh.

reviews.text:
Very disappointed, which I am very sad about.
I have been looking forward to trying 1126 for so long and had heard such good things. I ordered the chicken hibachi which started off with miso soup. The miso soup was cold when it came out. Then the chicken hibachi came out and I enjoyed it at first, until I found an eyelash in my food. I know for some people they are able to continue eating their food but this just really grossed me out. I told the waitress very quietly and politely and she just responded with oh I am sorry. The wait staff was okay. The food was fantastic and the vibe was great. My only complaints were the waiter was not super attentive to our table but was the to the table behind us. Also, hearing the door dash ding from the bar degraded the experience.

Went for a friends birthday and loved the food and drinks! Especially liked the strawberry cocktail, super refreshing. Very clean and the service was great! Ive always loved 1126. Decided to take my fiancée here tonight. And knew the google reviews didnt have enough photos of the drinks and menu so here you go!

Some of the best sushi in all of Columbus. The menu is large and they have something for everyone.

name: Smashburger
address: 1840 N High St Space B-110, Columbus, OH 43201, USA

reviews.text:
This place is good was in the area originally planning to have lunch at Barrio but it was closed so passed by this place and went in.

Got a crispy chicken with sweet potato fries and my friend got the classic burger. My sandwich was incredible- bread perfectly toasted, chicken nicely cooked and the tomato and lettuce super fresh. The fries were also well done too.

I also love that they offer full sized mustard and ketchup bottles so you don’t have to create waste with little packages of ketchup.

Will definitely return and next time will try their shakes. They have plenty of space inside with a number of tables and booths. The workers were super polite. We interacted with three different people who cleaned our table and or wished is a good weekend. You don’t get this kind of service at McDonalds.

Well the customer service is great. I tried something different and try to mac and cheese. But if you're not, you got to find a place to park. It's a headache so I give them three stars but since customer service is so great I moved it up to four.

Great burger and the side of Brussels sprouts was well done. They went really well with the ranch provided. The strawberry dragonfruit drink was excellent. Service was pretty quick and all very polite. Inside was very clean as well as the restroom.

It is definitely a great news that another new restaurant around campus was open with many welcoming staffs. Their classic burger was freshly grilled with fast service. They were ready for the coming fall semester.
After several times of visiting, the service is always great. Burgers are juicy. Their app has a few offers. The place is clean with a nice bar for live games.

The burgers are awesome...

This was another adventurous dining experience but was well worth venturing downtown to the OSU campus area.  I really like the use of the old building, and the location is easy to find. The food was really good - I had the bbq burger with onion rings, which I enjoyed  - wifie had their mushroom burger without a bun and the grilled Brussel sprouts, which she loved. reviews.text: We had dinner with friends at Speck, a modern Italian restaurant, and it was our first time visiting. I really enjoyed it! My husband and I shared the Chianti Braised Short Rib and the Wedge Salad, while our friend ordered the Crab Spaghetti. The short rib was incredibly tender and flavorful, and our friend loved her spaghetti. The focaccia bread was served hot and was so tasty. The service was excellent, and the ambiance made for a great dining experience. I can’t wait to go back on our next trip to Columbus!

Speck is one of our favorite Italian restaurants in Columbus! The food is freshly prepared and the ambience inside the restaurant is amazing. Parking downtown is a little tricky so be sure to take that into account when coming. Their focaccia is impeccable and you truly can’t go wrong with anything you get. A little on the pricey side, but worth it 100%.

Delicious Food Italian food 🥵, great modern experience, but a bit slow. Definitely recommend the bread and the sausage ragu, and pretty much everything. I went during lunch, which didn't have all of the dinner menu 😭. It was also cool to see them make the noodles through the top window. Overall great experience!

Pretty sure Speck is my new favorite Columbus spot for a nice dinner. We ate GOOD there. Unlike other higher end Italian joints, I didn’t leave here still feeling hungry. Their portion sizes are just right and the quality is literally so damn good. The service is TOP DRAWER. Shoutout to Zoe for making our first experience ((and my birthday)) a truly memorable dinner.

Best part? We did a couple starters, entrees, desserts, and drinks and very much did NOT spend an arm and a leg. It’s insane how incredible this place is and you’re doing yourself a disservice by not getting there ASAP.
Kaitlyn, our waitress, was absolutely phenomenal. This was our first time dining at  Speck and we were thoroughly impressed. Fabulous food, exquisite service and welcoming atmosphere.

name: Paulie Gee's Short North
address: 1195 N High St, Columbus, OH 43201, USA

reviews.text: Finally tried Paulie Gee’s after quite a few folks have suggested it on our quest to find some great pizza in OH. Did NOT disappoint! The Square was phenomenal, flavour, quality, and texture all came together for a perfectly scrumptious slice. We also got the hellboywhite pizza, again fantastic and fresh ingredients… but it really was the pizza square that will keep me up at night till i get another!
Ordered the Cherry Jones pizza. One of the best fancy wood fired pizzas I've tasted. Sweet savory yumminess. Definitely recommend trying it out. Friendly fast service. Great ambiance.

If you’re a pizza enthusiast in Columbus, Paulie Gee’s in the Short North is an absolute must-visit. From the moment you walk in, the warm, rustic ambiance sets the tone for a fantastic dining experience. The dim lighting, exposed brick, and communal seating create an inviting and laid-back atmosphere that makes you want to stay awhile.

Now, let’s talk about the star of the show—the pizza. Simply put, it’s phenomenal. Their wood-fired pies have the perfect balance of crispy-yet-chewy crust, rich tomato sauce, and high-quality toppings that elevate every bite. Whether you’re a classic pepperoni fan or love adventurous combinations, there’s something on the menu for everyone. I love the Cheese Square.

Service was equally impressive. The staff was friendly, knowledgeable, and attentive without being overbearing. They were happy to offer recommendations and made sure our drinks were always topped off.

Paulie Gee’s isn’t just a pizza joint—it’s an experience. Whether you’re out for a casual dinner or a fun night with friends, this spot delivers on all fronts. If you haven’t been yet, do yourself a favor and grab a slice (or a whole pie) ASAP.

I went to Paulie Gee’s for the first time tonight but I e been to many other pizza places in Columbus before. I can co directly say this is the best pizza in Columbus.

THE CRUST! Its chefs kiss perfect. It has good structure but also gives a little and has good ratio with toppings. Wood fired adds a delightful taste and crisp.

One of the people I dined with got a deep dish and I was very impressed with this as well- super crispy cheese on the edges, and well incredible. I’m not sure if I’ll do a deep dish or a traditional next time
Because they are both so good.

The only criticism I’d say is we ordered the Caesar salad and it really was quite spicy and I didn’t expect it. I wish they had more sides and maybe even a dessert menu but they do pizza extremely well so I’m glad they at least do that and offer a lot of variety in terms of toppings and crust type!

I’ve heard to get the true deliciousness you should done in and not take this to go! I’ll be thinking about this pizza for a long time!

3/2/24: weeks came back a second time. Service was excellent but the deep dish was a little over cooked (burnt) on the bottom and was a bit disappointing.

**Pizza Review: Paulie Gee's - 9.8/10**

Alright, so I went to Paulie Gee's with high expectations, and let me tell you, they exceeded every single one. First off, the *Regina Pizza* basically kicked down the door to my taste buds and threw a pizza party. The mozzarella? Stretchier than my gym routine. The sauce? So fresh, it might’ve just been tomatoes living their best life five minutes ago.

Now, about the pepperoni—these little guys were curled up like they were sunbathing on the beach, collecting all that savory, greasy goodness like tiny meat chalices sent from the heavens. I may or may not have wept a little when I took my first bite. Don’t judge me.

Then there’s the crust. I’m convinced this dough is the result of some ancient pizza magic passed down through the ages. Crispy outside, chewy inside, like it’s doing a perfect yoga pose. Honestly, if I could legally marry this crust, I would’ve already sent out the invitations.

Final verdict: 9.8/10. Why not 10? Because I couldn’t fit a second pizza in my stomach, and that’s a crime against humanity.

address: 1145 Chesapeake Ave ste d, Columbus, OH 43212, USA

reviews.text: Made reservations at Watershed for their Valentine’s Day Dinner set menu, and it was definitely worth it. Our server asked right off the bat if there are any dietary restrictions, and when this was shared, she immediately discussed this with the chef who was able to change the dish to meet my dietary restriction (replaced beef tartare with a beet tartare and maintained the overall look and taste of the dish!). We had the paired cocktails with the set menu which were all unique and complimented the food well. Although the location is in a random alley, the place is much bigger than expected and has such a nice ambiance to it with comfortable seating.

This was such a disappointment. We ordered our first round of drinks, which I got a N.A. bee’s knees and my husband got one of the specialty cocktails. Please tell me why a drink that was comprised of no spirits more expensive than my husband’s cocktail. It tasted like watered down lemonade. My husband said his cocktail was very disappointing.

Our service was not very good. We were asking about the chef’s tasting and went to ask a question, and our waitress interrupted and rudely said, “We don’t have that.” And offered no apologies and reacted the same way to another question we had.

We got the chef’s tasting. The food was not good. My kale on my salad needed to be massaged much more (it was as if they just threw it on the plate) and it was hardly anything else. My husband’s wings were not crispy. For the second course, I chose the halibut and my husband got the braised short ribs. The carrots on my plate were completely undercooked. The fish was okay. My husband said the short ribs were good, but the cabbage was either raw or burnt, very randomly cooked. For dessert he chose the apply crumble and it was okay. It needed a reprieve from how sweet it was, such as salt or lemon zest.

We had to wait a very long time between each course, and it typically wasn’t our waitress who brought food by or to check on us.

It is extremely loud inside. We were on the verge of shouting to hear each other.

Extremely disappointed, and we will not be back. I have been also sharing with friends and family as I do not want them to waste their money. We would have been better off saving $160 and just getting McDonald’s.

Dined here for our 5 year anniversary. Our server was very welcoming and friendly. The Caesar salad was the best I have ever had. We added shredded short rib to both of our entrees (mushroom pasta & grilled zucchini) which was delicious!! Their craft cocktails were unique and flavorful as well. The icing on the cake was the hand written card they gave us with a gift card inside for our anniversary. Great experience overall and we would definitely return!

Top tier flavor profiles in drink and food. This includes non-alcoholic cocktails or "Mocktails". A rustic, modern bar with private outdoor seating and indoor seating that has a full view of their stills which is cool.

Drinks:

Great. I got a "thats all right folks" in Alcoholic, theb my second in non-alcoholic. I actually liked both equally. The alcoholic is made with their own brandy and they balance it well. The n/a was really good and had a great cherry quality without being too simple.

Food:

Got brussels sprouts, bread, and market fish which was halibut.

The brussels was very well done - perfect texture and well balanced with sweet and acidity. The skins were not mushy or overdone, but weren't underdone as if gnawing on uncooked roots. Very good.

Bread - butter was red onion and jam I think was a seasonal fall profile like a spiced apple butter. I highly recommend this dish. It's extremely well done.

My fish dish was absolutely fantastic. It comes with spinach and yoghurt and pistachio. This dish was absolutely astounding. The only item for improvement was portion size - a halibut for nearly 40 bucks I recommend a larger portion size. Luckily, my fellow diner had way too much food so I finished off their fries.

Fellow diner got the kb burger. While the flavor was good (I didnt try, just relaying), ingredients resulted in a product far too wet and ended up being visibly soggy even to me. I saw the bread moosh up so they recommended doing a more solid cheese and sticking to onion instead of onion jam.

The fries were good, but definitely on the salty side.

Definitely expensive but they certainly take pride in their work. I just recommend a few improvements because it was so expensive.

I’ve been here three times. The first time I thought it was great, the second I got drinks and appetizers and the third I had dinner with a few friends.

Overall this place isn’t a regular jaunt. Most recently I found the food to be particularly unimpressive (with the exception of the fritters), and extremely overpriced.

Not busy as we went there while students were not on campus

I hope to go there as much I can.
Pretty good breakfast sandwiches and pastries. Drip coffee is so so. Espresso bar pretty decent and barista good.

Went twice this week for the same salad...I let the cashier know the first time I didn't get onions in my salad..ordered the same today and the same thing happened..Lucky I checked my salad before leaving...the lady that put my onions in basically threw the onions in the bowl...I'd like to get treated like everyone else!!!!

name: Red Rabbit Ramen
address: 985 W 6th Ave, Columbus, OH 43212, USA

reviews.text:
Update (Dec 28, '24): Finally got a chance to try ramen here with the new ownership. The owners are very friendly and easy to talk to. It was nice meeting them. The ramen tastes absolutely delicious. Nothing has changed. They have more tables and chairs outside compared to how it was before, which I love. Still the best ramen in Columbus!

The best ramen place is Columbus but unfortunately they are going to close very soon. I have tried vegetarian ramen at many restaurants in Columbus and none of those places come anywhere close to this place in taste. The broth was very flavourful and creamy. Cannot recommend this place enough to all the ramen lovers. My wife does not like ramen but even she liked this place. I hope that they sell this place to people who would run it well. Fingers crossed.

Update!
We finally grabbed some ramen from the new management and it was just as good!!!

Everything is absolutely delicious!!!! So so so fresh! The ramen is perfect to warm up on a cold day!  (We got one of each, they were all great! The spicy ones definitely have a kick!) We also got the Shishito Peppers Yakitori and Chicken Yakitori but those were devoured before I could get a photo haha very good. But also the Yaki Ongiri?!?! I didn't know rice balls could be that scrumptious.

Hands down the best ramen in Columbus. Food is made right in front of you and the employees are so kind. Excellent food and customer service. I go almost every week. I have tried everything on the menu but the spicy miso is my favorite!

Genuinely one of the hidden gems of the Columbus Ramen scene. I got the spicy miso and holy heck, that thing was so flavorful and had a serious (but not painful) kick. Really high grade broth and noodles. One of the best in the city. Not to mention they are super super friendly. Give this place a go!

Easily one of the best meals I've had in Columbus. Fantastic ramen (recommend the spicy miso or kimchi ramen) with a surprisingly flavorful oat milk based vegan broth. They do not skimp out on Chashu (which are thick and have great umami), and the noodles have a nice chewy texture.

Be sure to try the yakitori as well. Has a wonderful smoky aroma that can contend with any izakaya in Japan.

Columbus is very lucky to have such an awesome ramen spot, and it's a yatai to boot!

name: Traditions at Kennedy
address: 251 W 12th Ave, Columbus, OH 43210, USA

reviews.text: This dining hall is relatively accessible because of the height of seats, availability of food and the height of the entrance desk where you swipe in at. I appreciate how the food is served at a lower height which is greatly accommodating to wheelchair users, but the seating options in the largest dining place are difficult to maneuver around because of how closer together the tables and seats are, which allows for maximum seating options but does not really account for individuals in wheelchairs. On a positive note, I feel that the sensory environment is not too overwhelming at certain hours because the music is kept low and the area is kept clean but the large amount of people present at peak hours can be very overstimulating. Menus are up high above the food stations and can be difficult to read for people with visual impairments so I feel that they could do better at providing braille labels closer to the food rather than one larger menu off to the side. However, the staff is greatly accommodating and I appreciate their efforts in making this dining hall as accessible and comfortable as possible.

This is a nice dining hall. I went here and was satisfied with my experience. It has a wide variety of food, such as chicken breast’s, rice, hot dogs, and french fries. They have an allergen free station serving brown rice and other food, as well as a dessert station with cookies. There’s plenty of seating, and a seasoning station with Cajun, red pepper, Tabasco hot sauce, mustard, ketchup, and more. I gave this dining hall five stars because the food was better than I expected and because it has a nice seasoning station.

The employees are pretty nice, but the university policy on getting a clean plate each time you go back to get more food, along with the slightly subpar quality and variety of food makes it a quite average dining experience. It is a college dining hall, so maybe don’t have your first date here.

The people who actually put your food on the plate are nice, really amazing people. My one problem is this dude that walks around like he's the boss or something and just yells at everyone. Maybe I'm overreacting, but he hasn't put a smile on my face like the rest of the workers have.
Food is pretty pathetic, but It's a college dining hall so I'll take it.

Traditions at Kennedy, of the food halls, has the best food but not much of it. While traditions at Scott has way more options, they're not always that good. Kennedy has way better food, but there aren't many options. I recommend Kennedy as somewhere to go not every day, but every so often. To best show the difference, traditions at Scott has pre-made pancakes from some factory somewhere. Traditions at Kennedy has pancakes that are made by a chef in front of your eyes, and are still warm when you get them.

name: The Capital Grille
address: 1827 Olentangy River Rd, Columbus, OH 43212, USA

reviews.text:
Plenty of new highend steakhouses opening lately here in Cols.  This one is from the famed Darden Restaurants company that operates the Long Horn and Olive Garden chains.
The Capital Grille has a higher price point than Long Horn. The ambience is luxuriously attractive with a wine rack room encased in glass, dark wood, burgundy colors, mood lighting and white tablecloths.  We came here to try their dry aged steak which tastes amazing and perfectly cooked to your temperature.  We also ordered their famous wagyu burger, which is a pretty good deal paired with great wine and sides. We allowed their manager and chef to order for us their top sides and desserts to go with our steak and burger, and they were excellent (see pics for more).  Great selection of wines.
Overall, a great place to dine especially for a celebration, birthday, romantic dinner or after office get together.
The have valet but there is plenty of parking.  The service was quick and the staff very attentive.  Highly recommended!

We had the most romantic and delicious anniversary dinner at The Capital Grille in Columbus. I made the reservation online and just added a little note that said that it would be our first time there and that it was our anniversary.  They had a table beautifully decorated with little heart confetti, a single long-stemmed red rose, and a card. They also brought out a champagne 🍾 toast for us, which was lovely. We ordered delicious drinks (I had an amaretto sour and he had the blackberry side car) and for an appetizer we had the lobster and crabcake, it was by far the best we've ever had and highly recommend it! Our meals were yummy and cooked to perfection 🤌 I had the strip, he had the veal and we shared the Creamed corn with bacon and augratin potatoes.  They also had a bread basket with ample varieties included.  We ended with the anniversary creme brulee topped with fresh berries and it was outstanding! Our waiter was Anthony and he was so kind, engaging,  and responsive-we couldn't have asked for a better anniversary dinner. ❤️ Thank you The Capital Grille! We can't wait to come back.

Impeccable service from start to finish! The food was amazing but the service was even better! It seemed like the entire staff was looking out for us. Jordan, our waiter, took very good care of us also. It was my birthday and my entire table was treated like royalty. He paid attention to the small details, which we loved. Someone in my party asked if the rose bouquet, that was on display in the middle of the restaurant, was real because he is a flower lover. Next thing you know, Jordan came back with a rose for me and one for him. We were blown away! This was an amazing experience!

My wife and I picked The Capital Grill to celebrate our anniversary. We made a great choice. The staff, service, meal, and atmosphere were all exceptional. The staff acknowledged our anniversary both verbally and also with nice touches including decorations and a card at the table and a special dessert. We will be back.

We hosted a large dinner in one of their private dining rooms and had a prefix menu set. It was the perfect evening... amazing service, DELICIOUS food, great acoustics in the room... Lots of dark wood with a slightly masculine vibe, it is nicely decorated. (You would NEVER know this is the old Champs restaurant)!! The crab cakes were DIVINE!!! The steak, one of the best I've had in a long time! Every year, we usually host this large dinner at Hyde Park but decided to try Capital Grille instead this time and many of the guests said they enjoyed the experience MORE than Hyde Park!!! We'll certainly be returning for our annual dinner next year and I'll be visiting at some point myself before then!! Definitely check it out if you haven't already!

name: Galla Park Social
address: 900 N High St, Columbus, OH 43215, USA

reviews.text:
From the moment I stepped into Galla Park Social, I was greeted with warm and friendly service. The atmosphere was inviting, with just the right amount of ambiance to create a fun and enjoyable dining experience.

The drinks were exceptional, with a wide variety of options to choose from. The bartender was knowledgeable and made expert recommendations based on my preferences.

The food was the star of the show. Each dish was thoughtfully prepared with high-quality ingredients, resulting in flavorful and fantastic meals. The chef truly showcased his culinary skills with each plate that came out of the kitchen. From the appetizers to the entrees, every bite was a delight.

One of the highlights of the evening was when Chef Ryan himself came out to speak with us about our meal. His passion for cooking was evident in the way he described each dish and its ingredients. It was a special touch that added to the overall dining experience.

The service was fast and efficient, with our server checking in on us regularly to ensure we had everything we needed. The staff was friendly and attentive, making us feel like valued guests.

Overall, I had a wonderful time at Galla. The drinks, food, service, and atmosphere were all top-notch. I would highly recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a memorable dining experience. From the moment you walk in the door, you can tell that this establishment takes pride in everything they do, and it truly shows in the final product. I can't wait to return and see what other culinary delights Chef Ryan has in store for us.

Overall 7/10 not bad, but not for me

Very nice restaurant with friendly extremely friendly staff. Came for my brother’s birthday and made a reservation via open-table. It was for Sunday Afternoon so even though we switched reservation times, they still had our table ready and we were the only people there besides a few at the bar(it was NFC/AFC championship night). Our waitress was super friendly and explained everything that was asked. Amazing ambiance, perfect for their midnight club scene.  All of the food took a very long time to come out, but when it did, it was delicious and hot. As i previously said, it was AFC/NFC night so i give the chef a brake, there was most likely only one and we ordered 7 plates. I had the salmon, which was super tender 8.3/10. I will post the rest of the food my family had, they all said it was pretty good. You’re really paying for the location and ambiance. As a restaurant, it’s not bad, but I would personally go elsewhere. If you want a drink or a quick bite with a small group and you’re in the area, I would recommend it.
Parking is tricky, i recommend rides share if possible. The parking spots behind the building are for UDF, with a few unlabeled spots, but they seem like tow-away traps. First come first serve parking on E 1st Ave.

The food, the service, the drinks🤌🤌🤌we had the short rib bao buns, chicken & manchego dip, gallafornia chicken club, salad with grilled chicken,  stuffed chicken, and chocolate cake. 4 drinks we had the bubbles & berries, lychee twist, galla getaway & the oldest fashioned. Everything was so good and our server katie was the best! The only downside 4 us was how loud the music was. We came here 2 catch up with our friend who was in town 4 business and we are road tripping so we decided 2 meet up. Dinner & drinks sounded good but didn't know we would be eating while the music was loud enough that we felt like we were at the club. If this was 20 yrs ago we woulda been cool, but as we are old in our 40s we did not like it. It's a college town tho so we get it. Other than that guys please check this place out!

Great vibe and GREAT happy hour prices. Restroom was flooded so floors were wet all the way to the bar and only two stalls were functioning. Appetizers were yummy. Entrees and cocktails were underwhelming. Dessert wasn’t great. Staff was super nice (especially the bartenders) but unorganized. Wouldn’t recommend for dinner with larger groups nor corporate functions. All in all, do give it a try during happy hour with friends solely for the cheap prices and cool ambiance.

My wife and I tryed the Galla Park Social a few weeks ago during happy hour on a Friday night and wasn't sure what to expect. We tryed the Chicken Tenders with fries, Chicken & Manchego Dip, Short Rib Bao buns, Veggie Fried rice and the Spicy Tuna poppers. Something was off with the fried rice, it a little sour taste to it that tastes like lime. The Short Rib bao buns were ok.The spicy tuna were ok, I think it was just a texture thing for me. The hand breaded tenders and Chicken dip were our favorite. The portion sizes for the happy hour has to be one of the best portion sizes we've had and they didn't skimp on them even though it was happy hour. We also tried a few of the cocktails which were, the Watermelon Margarita, the Lotus and the bubbles & berries. As well as three of the happy hour maragritas which were all refreshing. I HIGHLY recommend the Galla Park Social, the server and staff was very attentive. I can't wait till our next visit!!!

name: Cazuelas Mexican Cantina
address: 2321 N High St, Columbus, OH 43202, USA

reviews.text:
Stopped in to see how if we found a new regular spot- we have not! The lunch portion fajitas were good and a good portion.

The chicken tenders and fries caused me angst.
They charge a $4 up charge for anyone over 12 getting the same portion of food- this always blows me away. I asked the server and he told me he would ring it at the 7.95 under 12 price. I told him we were prepared to leave as I wasn't paying $4 more since they didn't offer a hi Ken tenders appetizer for my son who doesn't enjoy Mexican fare. We could have and should have just left, but he confidently indicated it was not big deal, "I got you". We ordered and enjoyed some of the chips and salsa provided. We also had water to drink.

When they brought the chicken tenders and fries I was suprised by what I saw. They literally cut a tender in half and we got 2 chicken tenders and fries, and as you can see from the inside, little chicken inside. 🤯 my mind was blown 😂 we laughed and decided to just eat and we could grab my son something in the way home if he was still hungry.

Then the bill came and the server didn't have me, as you can see it was charged as the price with $4 more. After a long discussion with him (he tried to say maybe it was the service fee that was different 3% service charge for using a credit card! I explained that the record shows the cost of $4 more and 3% of $100 would only be $3 so that couldn't be it...the manager came over and he explained the policy and how he doesn't set prices. I explained that I understood, but we were going to leave until the server told us he would just charge the $7.95.

The manager didn't know how to refund the bill to correct, had to call someone, ended up reprinting the record and took my card again. The server came over and said he did it right, must have been the POS...um no - the machine doesn't know how old someone is...

Just own it dude. Ultimately, I am waiting to see when the credit occurs, they did not provide me with a credit slip and there are 2 charges on my credit card as of today.

I don't think we will be back.

My boyfriend and I come here about 1-2x a week, and whether it’s with friends or for a date we always have a great time! Our server Carlos is always awesome and very attentive and as someone who’s picky with Mexican food, I’ve never had a dish here that I haven’t enjoyed. Just waiting on the mexican ice cream to come back🤞🤞

Cazuela is an excellent Mexican restaurant that offers a true taste of authentic Mexican cuisine. The dishes are flavorful and well-prepared, making it a great spot for anyone who loves Mexican food. The atmosphere is inviting, and the staff is friendly, adding to the overall enjoyable dining experience. Whether you’re looking for a casual meal or a place to enjoy with friends and family, Cazuela is a solid choice.

Excelente servicio y saludos al Manager Angel de parte de Albert y su hermanastro!
Amazing. The food was delish! The service was great too. We sat on the patio and shared a Margarita pitcher.  I had the birria tacos. So good.

I've been to Cazualas many times and the food is always absolutely fantastic. It's what keeps me coming back.

Unfortunately what keeps me from coming is how terrible the service is here consistently. Most of the time is pretty standard, but some days (when they aren't even busy) it takes 10-15 minutes to find our waiter/waitress. I had to ask 3 different servers for our checks the last time we came in. There seems to be a heavy focus on to-go orders so maybe I should try that instead since the food is very good.

name: SŌW Plated
address: 1625 W Lane Ave, Upper Arlington, OH 43221, USA

reviews.text:
I love Sow Plated’s brunch! I appreciated that they let us finish our appetizers before serving our entrees, and the service is always very hospitable.

The beet and harvest salads were delicious and had the best textual contrasts and flavors. And the sweet potato biscuits were so buttery and warm. The egg sandwich needed to be salted more, but this is just my preference; others may find it perfectly salted. For dessert I ordered the chia seed pudding and the berry crumble. Both were good but I preferred the chia seed pudding since it wasn’t as sweet.

Our party of three had a wonderful dinner experience. Our server was excellent and so was every dish we ordered. Pleasant venue. Will return when in Columbus again. There were so many menu choices and we will try others next time!

SŌW Plated is the reason we brave the Ohio weather when visiting Columbus. This place is our go-to for healthy eats that actually taste amazing—like, “Is this kale flirting with me?” amazing. The food is fresh, the atmosphere is cozy (think Pinterest meets your favorite blanket), and the staff? They’re so friendly you’d swear they were secretly trained at Disney World. Whether you’re craving something wholesome or just want to pretend you’re a health guru for the day, SŌW Plated delivers. Bonus: they make eating veggies feel like a treat, not a chore. 10/10 would SŌW again!

Wonderful food for all dietary restrictions! I ended up changing my order after discussing our servers favorites and I was not disappointed! The juices were fabulous and the plates were large. It was tasty and healthy! Win win!

Had lunch yesterday.  There was a little snafu with a slight delay in the server getting to our table.  She apologized sincerely and was very gracious and helpful. Took excellent care of us. The manager Richard also came to our table and could not have been nicer and more accommodating.  He clearly cares greatly about creating an inviting atmosphere and ensuring customers enjoy their food with inquiries about our meals and experience which was all very pleasant.
The cauliflower appetizer was spectacular!  Very flavorful and tasty.  Loved it!  My main meal was the Mediterranean bowl which was also absolutely delicious! Would definitely return and order both of those items again. Beautiful atmosphere, lovely energy with friendly, engaging, helpful staff.

name: Third & Hollywood
address: 1433 W 3rd Ave, Grandview Heights, OH 43212, USA

reviews.text:
Made a reservation for a party of 12 (Saturday 5:45pm with a hard out by 7:30pm for the next party), had a great time overall! Valet parking right next to the restaurant was nice and allowed us not to worry about finding parking in the area.

Food and service were solid. Restaurant vibes are nice. The fish sandwich was delicious.

Have now been for both dinner and brunch, both experiences were great with brunch being my favorite. Commonly owned with Northstar and Brassica, the food is fantastic as expected. The dinner menu doesn’t differ as much as I’d like from Northstar, but brunch is worth the trip. I loved the jazz and laidback but upscale vibes.

My boyfriend and I were visiting from Michigan and Third & Hollywood was highly recommended. We went yesterday during lunch and we loved the food. The service was great . Everyone was so nice and welcoming. If we are ever in the area again we will definitely be back 🙂

My work team had our holiday gathering here tonight. The setting was really cozy and the fireplace was great. Service was a little slow, but we were there right before the dinner rush. I had the corn and clack bean burger with an arugula salad. We got the cheddar and herb biscuits for the table, they were the best things. I got an apreol spritz for my cocktail. All in all it was a great experience and I'd like to go back. My meal was about $35 for myself if that helps give reference.

The weekend brunch is highly underrated, but not to be missed! We were greeted with a warm fire and lovely ambiance of live music on a crisp fall morning. Third and Hollywood has a very cozy, dimly lit vibe that is great for celebrating a special occasion, date nights, happy hour and as we recently found out the best brunch in the 614!

Having long been on a quest to find the best cinnamon roll in Columbus, we have finally found it! As a vegetarian my go-to dish is the vegetarian mixed grill. A common mistake restaurants make with vegetarian/vegan dishes is not making it filling/hearty enough but I always come home with leftovers here! The artichoke hearts are another staple dish here that can not be missed.

Made me late to class several times due to taking 30+ min to make a cup of coffee
A perfectly fine campus dining experience. Very few options, perfectly adequate taste, and not much making it stand apart from anywhere else on campus. I like the Pizza Bagels.
Excited to have the bagel sandwiches again this fall!

reviews.text: Great food at a great price!  You can see by my picture of the shrimp and steak with noodles that the plates are massive!  Great flavor.  Soda is bottles or cans, no fountain.  Mine was $12.95 for Hibachi shrimp and steak-I may have paid extra for the lo mein instead of rice.  Our order was 2 large orders of General Tso's chicken, 1 steak and shrimp hibachi with noodles, crab rangoon (6) and 3 bottles of soda for $57 plus tip.  Easily enough for 5 more meals with our left overs.

I had an amazing experience at Taste of Orient! The food was fresh, delicious, and full of flavor. Every dish we tried was cooked perfectly, from the popcorn chicken, to the spring rolls. The fried rice was light and fragrant.

The staff was incredibly friendly and made us feel welcome right away. The service was quick, and they were happy to answer any questions about the menu. The restaurant itself was clean, cozy, and beautifully decorated, creating a relaxing atmosphere for our meal.

Overall, this is one of the best Chinese restaurants I’ve ever visited. I would highly recommend it to anyone looking for delicious food and great service. I can’t wait to come back and try more dishes!
Cashier is back there cutting food and touching handles with his bare hands rubbing his nose and all type of stuff. Then they charging you twice for food.

I've gotten take out from here twice now. Super delicious food and great portions for a great price. This is my new go-to for Chinese food here in Columbus. I've tried the sweet and sour chicken, general tsos, crab rangoons, and fried pork dumplings. Everything has been tasty, hot, and fresh. Can't wait to try more from here!

I have been here several times for American Asian food. Highly recommend their pad Thai and the pineapple fried rice! Green curry also tastes great. Their items are cheap coming with a large portion. But some dishes could be terrible, such as the hibachi combo. I also feel that their AC is always broken, never fixed.

address: 2885 N High St, Columbus, OH 43202, USA

reviews.text: Delicious pizza in a vibrant restaurant with beautiful art and tasteful decor throughout. The vegan pepperoni and peppers pizza was one of the best pizzas I’ve ever had and the mean green salad was tasty, too. Service was so warm and thoughtful. The lunch special was a great deal, too ($11 for a pizza + $3 for a side salad). Can’t wait to go back!
Great place, food was awesome, took a bit to get someone to take our order, but after they did, they were attentive to our needs, recommend going here.

First time in...

This is a great little place. It checks all the boxes. The waitress was AWESOME, and the service was spot on. The atmosphere was really upbeat. the decor was really cool.  The food was delicious.  We had the fried cauliflower as an appetizer, which I strongly recommend.  And we each had a pizza and a salad special, which was awesome - I really don't think you can go wrong with any of their pizzas, and the make a great salad also. The other dishes look amazing, too.

I’m a native New Yorker who made it a point to find the best pizza in Columbus. I originally found the German Village location. Loved it! Was very excited when the Clintonville location opened. Love the atmosphere, especially by the bar area. Was giddy when they opened up the Dublin location:-) Their lunch special is truly special! Their individual pizzas and their salads are fabulous. The menu is great! My only gripe is the nonalcoholic beer should be less expensive.

Kid friendly and servers were very nice. Bar service and speed from order to table were slow but not unheard of. Ordered a dessert and it never came. Meatballs were spicy (but delicious) and the Arancini was delicious. Pizzas were between a 6/10 and an 8/10 depending on the pie and I really love the Quattro Formaggio. Will be back for sure.

address: 2110 Tuttle Park Pl STE #43, Columbus, OH 43210, USA

reviews.text: I had high expectations of the food and service here but it’s rather disappointing. I had a weekday breakfast buffet $16 since I was in a rush and did not want to wait for ala carte order but the variety is sad and the food is not warm. They only had a few hot food like scrambled eggs, sausage/bacon, hashbrown and pancakes. There are some fruits but other than that it’s not worth the money for the quality. Will not recommend the buffet breakfast

Literally the most disappointing breakfast I have ever had. I got an omelette and it took over 20 minutes to come out and we were the only people in here. bland and drenched in oil. i couldn’t even eat through half of it. even the fruit was underripe. sad truly. way overpriced.

Ate here with a group of friends last night before visiting the OSU planetarium. The atmosphere was not particularly interesting, just a cavernous room in a hotel. The meal was  nothing to write home about, although I did like the bread and pesto butter. Plenty of options for vegetarians were available, and in fact these were the most modestly-priced choices. The servers were polite enough, but a bit disorganized, and slower than one would expect given that it was not the least bit crowded. We needed a place to dine in the middle of campus, and it served the purpose well enough.

Not what I expected when I made my Valentine's Dinner reservation. There was a set menu which our server told us we could not alter (when I made the reservation, no such set menu was mentioned). My glass of wine took at least 10 minutes to arrive. My appetizer was the only highlight of the meal, but while I was looking outside at the snow, the server took it away before I had finished without asking. A few moments later she returned to check on our meals (which arrived as we were still working on the first course) and we asked if she was boxing up the appetizer since I still had about a quarter of it left.  She said no, but fortunately it is on their every day menu so we can come back any time and have it again.  She did not offer to bring another even though we reminded her that I had not yet finished it. There was a large chunk of melon in my husband's Caesar salad, which she said it not normal.  Dinner was less than satisfactory, but having both worked in the restaurant industry for years, we did not complain because it was still edible.  We overheard the server near our section describing featured items on the menu as well as informing other diners that if there was an item not listed on tonight's set menu that they really had their hearts set on, they could still order that (our server told us the set menu was our only option).  Overall, we were very displeased with our first experience here and will not return.  As alums, we had high hopes for The Blackwell Bistro based on pictures from the website and the viewable menu.  Unfortunately, we left disappointed and ended up ordering a pizza after we returned home.

Lunch/Dinner Items may arrive at the table differently than described in the menu.

They are generally understaffed, but those who work there are nice.

Breakfast buffet was well-priced and the food looked good; however, many items were cold and/or old.  They also need real butter.  "Whipped buttery spread" is nasty stuff.

name: Brekkie Shack
address: 1060 Yard St, Columbus, OH 43212, USA

reviews.text:
Had high hopes after perusing menu online. Long line wait, no paper menus in line. Once soem arrived they were dirty.

70 dollars with tip. Granted, part of that is under estimating portion sizes which were large on most things except the vegetarian hash.

Fellow diner enjoyed their food alright which was the BLT and a deep fried bagel dish. I liked the chili oil with the latter. Also their french fries they let me try them and they were really good and crispy.

I got a maple latte (which was good), vegetarian hash and an avocado toast.

You seat yourself and provide yourself everything you need (flatware, seasonings, etc). Most booths and surfaces were dirty, including the screen I had to touch to sign for payment.

Hash was okay although it was bland and lacked firmness and color. Eggs were not cooked properly as the whites were not fully done, resulting in slimy texture. Flavor profiles were good. Avocado toast was disgusting. Not only was it not toasted, but someone in the kitchen must have poured on lemon juice way too much. Soggy and lemony.

People were nice enough, no complaints there. Just the food it wasn't worth the price points in my opinion. Maybe it was a fluke.

So many food things here. First this is locally owned and I'm always happy to spend locally when I can. The food was delicious. I had the chicken salad tacos and omg so good. All of it. The bakery items look amazing and you'll be tempted to try them all. I'm not a coffee drinker but lots of people were coming in for their fav.
Food was good with sizable portions. Latte was great. We enjoyed sandwiches and a cream stuffed pastry.

The restaurant is conveniently located just a few minutes drive from the OSU campus. As you step inside, you will be welcomed by the warm and inviting ambiance. The well-lit interior is immaculate and features a charming decor that sets the perfect tone for a delightful dining experience. The friendly staff is always ready to help and make your visit pleasant. The menu offers many options to cater to everyone's taste buds, including a special kids' menu. If you prefer to dine outdoors, the restaurant provides limited but cozy outdoor seating. Overall, it is a must-visit spot for anyone looking for a delicious meal in a welcoming and comfortable setting.
Visited for our first time this past Saturday, was so good we had to come back Sunday morning. Felt like we were in South Florida - nicely done. We will be back the next time we are in Columbus.

address: 10 E 12th Ave, Columbus, OH 43201, USA

reviews.text:
Very good soup. I tried the spicy beef noodle soup since I assumed it to be their staple recipe. Broth and noodles were amazing. Taking one star off though due to the beef chunks being very tough and wouldn’t consider it top quality meat. Nonetheless this place was very good and I’m sure I’ll return solely for the noodles and broth. Nothing beats that!

EDIT: They upgraded their beef and I am impressed ! 5 stars in all aspects. A great meal, especially if you need some soup to clear your sinuses after a cold. Bravo.
Everything I’ve had here has been delicious from the noodle soups to the dumplings! Seriously some of the best food around campus

We ordered the spicy beef noodle soup and Liu Zhou River Snail Noodle Soup. These were both delicious. Flavor has depth and blends well together. Fast service. We will definitely be back to try out their vast menu.

There was nothing fancy about the atmosphere. Gives authentic mom and pop restaurants in Asia there you just get a table. They bring the food out to you and clean it as well. Utensils are self serve.

Doing a college drop off and found this amazing gem. Not a lot of seating but if you can find a table get it to eat there so it is fresh. If not now worries, get it to go and find a spot on campus to enjoy. Either way you won’t be disappointed.

Orderes Spicy Beef noodle soup, tomato and beef noodle soup, yang Zhao fried rice, and spicy chicken with rice.

Spicy chicken came with more vegetables than chicken.

Beef noodle was served in beef cubes, not bee slices. The beef doesn't have any seasoning and tastes bland on its own.

It's OK. Not the best, but it's OK for Chinese food.

name: Rollz Rice Indian Kitchen
address: 16 E 16th Ave, Columbus, OH 43201, USA

reviews.text:
Ii am a big fan of Indian food and love to try all the Indian restaurants. This place not bad.
I don’t like the idea of the bowls, the Indian foods featured in its sauces and each type of food has its unique taste, when they serve the food in bowl and mixes all the Seuss together in one dish which ruins the taste.
I can say this is the first time I didn’t enjoy the Indian food and I believe if they served the dressing and sauces separately would be prefect.
BTW i asked them to have them separately but shockingly they said that would be extra cost!

Owner/manager is great. I had mistakenly ordered at a different location, he re-made it at this location without any extra charge.
Food is delicious and a good portion.
Gets a bit expensive with add-ons, but base price is alright.
As always amazing food. The naan bowls are just too good. This Rollz Rice serves alcohol and it's actually decent price. $2 house lager and $10 margarita flight.

I was so excited when I saw this place popped up, but I’ve honestly only went a handful of times.

It’s one of the few restaurants where you really have to know what you do and don’t like when it comes to Indian food. I came in here first time and did NOT like what I got, but I did some research and admit that I should’ve known I wouldn’t like it.

Going back, I got some spinach curry and it was second to none. Absolutely amazing. Their cilantro rice is much more authentic than most you’ll find, and their fries are to die for.

Their alcoholic mango lassi was also quite good, would definitely recommend it.

Hope this place gets the love it deserves 🙏 food is always hot, fresh, and extremely well spiced.

A great Indian fast food restaurant is open near campus. The service was fast and friendly. They had various protein options and the spicy chicken was tasty. The curry rice bowl tasted good and fresh but different from the one that I have in authentic Indian restaurants. It is a little weird to mix everything together. It is more like an American Indian dish.

name: Rush Bowls
address: 262a W Lane Ave, Columbus, OH 43201, USA

reviews.text: Great little smoothie place. They have a large selection of different smoothies and bowls with quick service. Especially recommend the rush bites, specifically the banana bread variety; absolutely delectable.

This was my first time coming here and I loved trying their creation! I got the avocado bowl and topped it with strawberries and coconut shavings. The bowl base itself was good, but it had just a bit too much pineapple juice. I absolutely loved the coconut shavings and granola bits. There's so many choices on their menu, you can try so many different things. They offer smoothies, acai bowls, and traditional bowls. Their prices range from $7-$10, depending on your add-ons and toppings.

This is a great spot for college students and and a great on the go, to-go spot. There's only a few stools and a long table top to sit at, so there's not much room. I think the location was good, for those walking, but it was difficult to park. Staff was absolutely friendly and Monica, the cashier, was super helpful and nice!

They offer a lot of different toppings, such as: chocolate chips, peanut butter, coconut shavings, strawberries, bananas, blueberries, etc. They also offer a lot of supplement add-ins, such as: matcha green tea, immune support, brain wave, etc.

Great place to stop in and get something healthy and fresh!

Went here for the first time today and got the peanut butter and jelly bowl and my husband jungle bowl.  The peanut butter and jelly was so good I don't know about my husband's lol.  Will definitely be eating there again

Love this place! Everything I get from here is so good and what I envision. It’s all made fresh including their peanut butter. My favorite is the chai’s mystique I’m obsessed with it and definitely recommend.
Knowledgeable and kind staff. Everything is so delicious!

name: Saucy Brew Works Columbus - Brewpub & Coffeehouse
address: 443 W 3rd Ave, Columbus, OH 43201, USA

reviews.text:
Fabulous but limited beer selection…BUT, some of the best beers I’ve had in Columbus.
Happy Hour! HELL YES! All drafts 4$ (and again, they are fabulous), and this huge pizza was under 10$

This was a disappointing experience. I was with a group of three, and it seemed like there was an issue with every order.

First, staffing appeared to be minimal—only one person was behind the bar. We ordered drinks using the QR code, but one of the beers was incorrect. We had to take it back to the bar, where they corrected the mistake, but they mentioned the order printed incorrectly on their slip, even though our receipt showed the correct selection.

One person in our group ordered nachos, only to find the chips were stale. Another ordered mac and cheese and was looking forward to the pretzel stick that was supposed to come with it—but it was missing. When we finally spotted a server and asked, they initially said it didn’t come with one. We pointed out that both the menu description and pictures showed otherwise. After checking with the kitchen, they returned a few minutes later and simply said they were out of pretzels—without offering a replacement.

I ordered a half-dozen wings, which took quite a while to arrive. When they finally did, there were only five. I flagged down a server, who mentioned it was her first day and wasn’t sure about the portion. After checking with the kitchen, she confirmed it should have been six. They offered to either bring out another wing or "make things right"—though it wasn’t clear what that meant. I opted for the extra wing, which took another 10 minutes to arrive. She then explained that the kitchen was training three new staff members, which likely contributed to the mistakes and delays.

Overall, the service and food quality were disappointing. Additionally, since this is a pay-on-your-phone system, you have to tip before receiving your food or service. I prefer to tip based on my experience, so this felt like an odd approach.

I wouldn’t recommend this place until they improve their staff training and overall operations.

You have to order thru an app which is super annoying. When you have to check on your food order you have to go up to the bar. Food service was very slow even though not busy. Had to take my pizza to go because of how slow it was. The pizza is really good and the drinks are also good.

My friends and I came and we all waited 2 hours for our food. All I got was a WRAP and pizzas were coming out left and right before mine. My friend got just a side of mac and cheese and it came out ice cold. When we brought it up to the wait staff was met with nothing but rude dismissals shrugging off the issue. All of this after tipping 25% too! Will never be returning.

This was my friends and I’s first visit to Saucy Brew Works. It was moderately busy, but by no means packed. We all ordered via QR codes within 5 minutes of each other. the first pizza did not come out until an HOUR and 15 minutes after. We did not receive a single notice from the waiters about the food taking longer than normal or of anything unusual. By the time the entire group got their food, we had been waiting for over 2 hours. The Mac and cheese was freezing cold when it came out after 2 hours, and the waitress did not say a single thing and left our table and did not come back when we told her of this. When we finally flagged down another waitress, she said the service has been slow all week. No apologies nor reasoning. We all tipped very generously prior to receiving the food as this is required through the QR code, and when we said that we wouldn’t have waited nor tipped if we had known we had to wait 2 hours, we were told we should’ve gone up to the bar to check on the wait before ordering. We all individually had to go up to the manager to request refunds, and even then no workers seemed to really care that their service had been over 2 hours with no explanations or apologies. We understand things happen, but the customer service was unlike anything we’ve ever seen. Very very disappointing.

It is one of my favorite restaurants around campus.
It's posted as if it 's good.  It said beef stroganoff now back for a limited time.  I love Beef Stroganoff but this was quite dry.

The food here is VERY high quality. Their menu has something for everyone. You can enjoy anything from macaroni and cheese, baked chicken parmigiana, Japanese pan noodles, or a homemade Rice Krispy treat, just to name a few.

We visited for my youngest. The menu was tempting. I got the Orange Chicken. The noodles were great! The veggies mixed in really added to the bowl. The chicken was perfect, well cooked.
My wife had Japanese noodles and they were tasty. The staff was nice, and it seemed like they were working well together. I wish we had a location near us.

Ordered a ceasar salad and potstickers through doordash in hopes of a decent meal to get through my overnight shift. The lettuce was soggy and there was barely enough dressing for half my salad. They wrote “sorry out” for the potstickers I ordered. This place is not worth a crappy $15 salad.

Salmon came out undercooked and my noodles came out dry and tasted like it was leftover from the day before. my husband said the lasagna tasted like it was microwaved, not fresh.
