She was gone 95% of the time we were there. Finally, she brought to go boxes and the check, also,  never cleared our table one time. We've been to a different bravo before and it was great, but not this location

Mid-week dinner at 6 pm. Restaurant was fairly busy but I got seated timely and served with no delays. Great pasta choices, from light to loaded. Many options for adult drinks. Pasta Woozie was delicious and light choice that provided good taste  and protein.

Monty was our waiter, he was very polite and courteous and helpful with our first time in Bravo 👏 🙌 👍 everything was first class and worth the price. My wife Sarah had the egg plant parmasan and I had the shrimp fra diavolo blackened suggested by Monty great choice. A little spicy so Monty suggested Alfredo sauce on the side 😋 👌 perfect. Definitely coming back when in town.

10/26/2024
Great dinner and great service at Bravo, last night! Everything was very nice! Beautiful atmosphere, delicious food, and our server was excellent!

Had a fantastic dinner last night at Bravo! We sat on the patio and really enjoyed the atmosphere! Aaron, gave us the perfect amount of attention and the dinner was absolutely delicious!

My experience at Bravo was amazing! I came here to celebrate my birthday!! The food was delicious!! My server, Aubrey had to be the best server that I have ever had!! First of all, she greeted me with a smile!! She was delightful!!  She always made sure that my drinks were filled without me asking!! She brought fresh hot bread with  oil to my table!! She was very attentive and pays very close to details, which really means a lot to me, as I am a vegetarian!!  I really appreciated having her as a server!!  I'm sure she is a pleasure having her as an employee!! Excellent service!!

reviews.text:
Great food and nice atmosphere! My wife and I got the crispy chicken sandwich, classic burger and fries. We split everything and we were so glad we did. The sandwiches had a really tasty sauce and the fried were cooked to perfection! I asked for their special sauce for their fries so we didn’t have basic ketchup to dip our fries in and that was also a great decision.

The service was friendly and the decor was very nice. We are so glad we found this place and would come back if we’re in the area again.

Love this place! My friends and I went for the first time tonight, and it was such a nice experience. The staff were kind and helpful and it was so awesome to see how proud they are of their work and how it gives them joy :) This was a great first experience! I didn’t get a picture of everything we ate, but all of it was delicious :)
The interior had cool paintings on the walls, leading to a nice and welcoming atmosphere. Overall the experience was absolutely amazing, would recommend coming here! My friends and I had a great time.

Tried Food Street restaurant based on a friend’s recommendation, and it didn’t disappoint!
The ambience inside is really nice and welcoming.
We ordered some chat and rolls—the rolls were absolutely the highlight, packed with flavor and cooked to perfection. The chat, however, was just average and could use some improvement.
I’d definitely recommend this place for their amazing rolls and look forward to trying more from the menu!

An unapologetically authentic Pakistani street food experience with delicious eats, great drinks, and a cozy yet energetic atmosphere. Definitely gets pretty packed on the weekends so plan accordingly and maybe call in advance

An absolute gem for food lovers! The ambiance is warm and inviting, perfectly complementing the incredible flavors of the dishes. The highlight for me was the live tandoor station at the front—you can watch the chicken being cooked to perfection, adding an authentic touch to the experience. Every bite transports you straight to the vibrant streets of Pakistan. A must-visit spot for anyone craving genuine Pakistani street food. Can’t wait to return!

name: Understory
address: 2571 Neil Ave, Columbus, OH 43202, USA

reviews.text:
I’ve been obsessed with Understory for quite a bit. I love the uniqueness of the building architecture and the original elements that remain throughout. I wanted a more moody vibe for our October wedding and it was the perfect setting. I was thrilled when the Fieldhouse event space upstairs was available. Haley was super helpful and answered any questions I had.

I was able to customize the menu to fit our needs and it was the perfect day for our intimate wedding. The space felt very cozy - we had around 80 guests. We got so many compliments about our day. It was perfect and I wish I could experience it all again!

I do recommend having a solid plan for setup/cleanup since you can’t leave decor overnight.

My husband and I had our wedding ceremony and reception at the private event space on the 2nd floor. We rented out the venue for the entire day, had a wonderful brunch and such a fun reception! Haley helped us plan our entire event and we can’t say enough great things about her. The staff who helped the day run smoothly were wonderful, calming, flexible, and professional. The food was delicious and drinks were excellent. The weather was also perfect and the balcony was well used during our reception. We loved having our wedding at The Understory, and it’s so fun we can go back to grab a drink or a bite and reminisce!

Visited on our trip to Columbus.  Excellent food.  Plating of the food made it visually very appealing.  Good options for vegetarians.  Very efficient and friendly staff.  Enjoyed the outdoor seating.  In all an excellent dining experience.

Conveniently Handicapped accessible by electric wheel, including restroom.  Have to take a service elevator to come from parking level to road, and the walkway to the elevator is a little tight in space.

We held an event with 80 people here, and cannot say enough positive things about the day! We rented the entire second floor with the terrace, which was wonderful for people to move about. Having the food and bar in a separate room was perfect. We had so many compliments on the food. It was all delicious and unique! The atmosphere was casual and pleasantly inviting. Debi was so helpful in determining the perfect menu selections and quantities, as well as room set up. Jen, Lila, Jerald, and Zoey were perfectly attentive and beyond helpful throughout the event. All the linens were in place when we arrived, which made set up go very quickly and smoothly. Very organized! Having an elevator was very convenient for some of our guests. This was such a great place to host an event, with a cool vibe and awesome food! Thank you all!

Loved the atmosphere, I love that it overlooks a wooded area and has a really nice brick patio. The inside is cozy and there’s a lot of natural light that comes in. I also enjoyed the plants.

As other reviews have mentioned, the food is a bit pricey for what you get / what it is. Overall the food was good, I got the chicken sandwich, my bf got the burger and pirogies and we each had a beer and in total it was nearly $70.
Once you order your food at the counter they bring it to you and then once you’re done, you clean up the dishes yourself. They have an area to serve yourself water and offer a small variety of board games.
I think overall it’s a nice place to maybe stop in have some drinks and share an appetizer but not necessarily have dinner since the menu is fairly limited.

The food was amazing. This was my first time eating meat in 5 years and I wanted to ensure it was halal. The temperature, taste, and texture was absolutely perfect. My new go to! Best hummus I’ve ever tasted. The rice is delicious and seasoned perfectly & the white sauce brings it all together. CHEFS KISS. Prices are great as well. Huge proportions.

Jetpack’s Burger Truck brings a delightful twist to the classic American burger right from the heart of Columbus. Visiting this vibrant blue food truck is a treat, not just for the palate but also for the eyes, with its colorful setup and inviting neon signs. Each burger, like the Jetpack Royale and Barkin’ Dawg, is a masterpiece of flavors with perfect layers of crispy bacon, spicy cheese, and their signature sauces that make each bite memorable.

Whether you’re grabbing a quick bite or hanging out with friends, Jetpack’s offers a fantastic experience that goes beyond just eating. Their commitment to quality and flavor shines through every item served.

So next time you’re in the area, swing by Jetpack’s Burger Truck. It’s not just about the burgers; it’s about enjoying the moment, one delicious bite at a time. For more details and visuals from my visit, follow me on Google Maps and Instagram @Riguinlo!

Best, burger, hands down. Fight me on it. Best prices in the city. The double smash burgers perfect and with crispy edges, bun soft and toasted perfectly, everything is fresh and flavorful. The owner is super kind! Go if you love and respect your taste buds, and a fantastic burger.
This place rules. Staff were super friendly. Food quality/price ratio is lacking in Columbus but this place is exceptional. The burger was delicious and fresh. Recommend to anyone.

A Burger truck that’s all about the burger. My friends and I were going somewhere else, but we’re pulled into the interesting vibe of the owners truck. He’s a very nice guy and he makes some amazing burgers. I got the Barkin Dawg burger and it was everything i wanted, and i couldn’t put it down.

I went here for the first time on 12/14. I've followed them for awhile on Instagram and was finally able to stop by, the hype was correct! The food is great and the value is excellent! Will definitely be coming back :)

name: Zundo Ramen
address: 2500 N High St, Columbus, OH 43202, USA

reviews.text:
Our time in Japan taught us to love ramen...and we're so glad we can enjoy top-level ramen also right here in Columbus! We've been to Zundo several times now and it has quickly become our favorite ramen restaurant in Columbus. The tonkotsu broth is so rich and flavorful. The distinct bit of ginger that comes through compared to other ramens in town also adds to its scrumptious  flavor. The charred high-end pork is amazing. reviews.text:
If you’re looking for an authentic and budget-friendly koshary experience in Cairo, Koshary King is a solid choice. This local eatery serves Egypt’s beloved national dish—a hearty mix of rice, lentils, pasta, chickpeas, and crispy fried onions topped with tangy tomato sauce and optional spicy chili. The portions are generous, the flavors are well-balanced, and the food is served fresh. While the restaurant doesn’t have a fancy setting, it delivers exactly what you’d expect from a classic koshary spot: quick service, simple yet delicious food, and an authentic local vibe.

However, like many casual dining places in Cairo, the overall cleanliness and maintenance of the area could be improved. The surroundings might feel a bit chaotic, and the streets often have litter, which takes away from the experience. But if you’re here for the food rather than the atmosphere, Koshary King won’t disappoint. It’s an ideal stop for travelers who want to taste real Egyptian street food without spending much. Just be prepared for a no-frills, local dining experience!

Koshary:
A new dish to me and one that has fun textures that all come together well. The sauce is subtle with a solid flavor, their hot sauce adds a very nice touch

Egyptian Rice Pudding: best rice pudding I've ever had! So good and not too too sweet. I want more

Never had anything like the Koshery, with its pasta, chickpeas, tomato sauce, fried onions, and spices. But I particularly enjoyed the chicken over rice and the unique, lemony sauce. My 10 year old daughter loves both of them. We will be going back. Wonderful addition to the neighborhood.

I lived in Egypt for a year and fell in love with the food there, especially falafels. I was so excited to try this place out because of the amazing reviews. I was hoping that the food would taste at least somewhat authentic, and I was looking forward to introducing my husband to tasty Egyptian food since I've raved about it so much.

We ordered the falafel sandwich and the koshary. Both dishes were nothing close to authentic and unfortunately neither was very enjoyable to eat. We were both disappointed.

I'm so confused how the reviews are so amazing, including from some people that say they've eaten authentic Egyptian food. I've eaten food from an Egyptian restaurant in San Francisco, and while not exactly like street food in Egypt, the falafel was delicious.

This falafel was nothing close to the flavor and texture of an authentic Egyptian falafel sandwich. The falafels didn't have the traditional amazing mix of spices and pops of flavor (true Egyptian falafels are made with fava beans instead of chickpeas, and have a mix of many tasty spices, including fennel), the tahini had the texture and taste of hummus, but with way too much cumin, the pita tasted like a cheap store-bought kind, and the overall texture of the sandwich was mushy, including the tomatoes. The koshary noodles tasted overcooked and the flavor of the sauce and the whole dish wasn't great.

The owner seemed nice and looked Egyptian so I thought the food would taste authentic. I'm glad so many other people enjoy this restaurant so the owner can get good business, but I'll continue my search for an Egyptian restaurant so that hopefully one day I'll be able to introduce my husband to tasty and authentic Egyptian food.

Hang out on Summit and enjoy some flavorful middle eastern food. We loved the falafel sandwich and the flavorful thick grainy hummus. Friendly owner. Did I mention the excellent baklava? We went back to buy more.

name: Dough Mama Clintonville
address: 3335 N High St, Columbus, OH 43202, USA

reviews.text: Not only were the staff a delight, but the whole vibe of the place is amazing. Some of the best food you could ever have. Walking into the dining room is a visual delight and the best music playing. I can't believe this place is real. Give me pickled onions on everything!!
Really good food and lots of fun items for sale as well. Definitely recommend their biscuits/quiche for a good breakfast or brunch option!

My hairstylist recommended I come here for morning brunch and Dough Mama did not disappoint! The menu is plentiful and had options I could eat with my dietary restrictions, the atmosphere was inviting to ALL, and most importantly, what an amazing queer friendly space here in Clintonville! The cashier was friendly and made the modifications to the food I requested. I got the BLT with roasted potatoes and a balsamic vinaigrette side salad, and paired it with a cereal milk latte. My partner got the biscuits and mushroom gravy dish and an orange juice. Everything was so satiating!!! A little on the pricy side but you get what you pay for, everything tasted fresh and homemade. Thank you Dough Mama, we will be back 🤩

Incredible, fresh, delicious food in a cozy spot and the friendliest staff! Everything we ordered - avocado biscuit, quiche, tuna melt, salad, scone was perfectly cooked with the tastiest seasonings and toppings. The friendly staff at the front told us that all their biscuits and pastries are made by hand! The scone, bread pudding, and biscuits definitely tasted homemade and were SO DELICIOUS.

We also ordered a variety of cold brews: the lavender maple cold brew, regular cold brew, and maple cold brew. We also had a matcha oat milk latte. The regular/plain cold brew had an excellent spectrum of coffee flavor with citrusy and herbal notes. The lavender latte had a perfect amount of lavender. The maple latte had a very subtle maple flavor and was not too sweet at all. The matcha latte was so incredible and inspires me to make it better at home too!

I will definitely come back to this amazing little brunch spot next time I’m in Columbus!

Dough Mama never disappoints. Neighborhood staple and great breakfast/lunch/brunch spot.

I have dreams about the GF Lemon Poppy Seed Muffin… it’s THAT good and gluten free. Come early… they usually run out the most popular baked goods depending on how busy the morning is but there is something yummy for everyone.

Seating includes outdoor Parisian café style on N High Street (can be a bit loud due to traffic but it’s fun watching frequent + diverse passerby’s in this central heart of the southern Clintonville neighborhood.

They also have a small indoor dining room and a larger outdoor patio out back surrounded by plants. That is the more intimate dining option and where I usually take friends from out-of-town for brunch.

name: Auzy’s Pizza & Chicken
address: 2864 N High St, Columbus, OH 43202, USA

reviews.text:
Solid spot for pizza and fried chicken. The pizza had a nice crispy crust and plenty of cheese, and the chicken was crunchy and juicy. Friendly staff, laid-back vibe. Cold-Subs were definitely a standout Service was fast & quick. Definitely worth it.
(Didn’t take any pictures of the fried chicken or Turkey sandwich because we ate it wayy too fast)

Auzy's sits inside the High St. Kitchen complex in that, it's a pickup ONLY spot. There is no seating for you because it's not a food hall, it's a business warehouse with multiple kitchens inside which you order from! With that said Auzy's is worth the hype and after trying 2 pizzas, chicken and chicken wings I would easily recommend their offerings. I can't imagine you'd be upset with their food and I'll add them to my personal list of some of the better spots for tasty chicken.
Wow oh wow, this place is amazing. The pizza and the chicken are equally good, which is no small feat. Would recommend to anyone looking for an excellent meal

This is neither a paid nor related review like someone stated below. I am a transplanted NYer and a true pizza snob. Auzy’s pizza is amazingly close to the real thing. The crust is crunchy on the outside and soft on the inside and that was after it was delivered! Which I have yet to find with any other so-called pizza spot in Columbus! Anyone giving a bad review is just jealous. My favorite is the meat lovers. Very generous toppings on all of the pizzas. The main attraction is the Fried Chicken and THE GRAVY!! 10/10! I didn’t know that I needed the gravy until I had the gravy! Do not sleep on it. Auzy makes it himself. Let me not forget to mention the wings! My grandkids are addicted to the Honey Garlic Lemon Pepper wings. They arrived crunchy and juicy, full of flavor! Again, this was after it was delivered! I have been a fan of Ana Shawarma for a long time but now my family is addicted to Auzy’s and I have recommended my friends too. Also, Great customer service every time!

There are a lot of paid or brother-in-law reviews here.  For starters, this pizza is not NY style.  I'll give them the fact that they have unique toppings, but the crust is more akin to Little Caesars or Gatti's.  Their fried chicken was really good and the hot sauce you get with the chicken was great.  If you want great chicken from a pizza place, this is a good option.  If you want great pizza though, I wouldn't go here.  Mikey's LNS is leagues better.

The spicy potato salad is fantastic, as is the spicy gizzard with cucumber salad.
The Chinese doughnuts are like fried air, unspeakably satisfying.
Great numbing sichuan pepper chile seasoning and spice on most all dishes.
8.7/10 food, with a 9.5/10 being perfect

Fun authentic Chinese vibe. Great food,  the portions are large, so unless you are taking out, or a giant~  share an entree.
Authentic northeastern Chinese food. I like it a lot. Very delicious cuisine.

Great unassuming small dining room Chinese restaurant. I enjoyed the large menu with some recommended specials and an entire “popular American” dishes section. I had the cumin seed lamb and fried dumplings. Solid all around, took a minute to get used to the cumin seed texture but I loved it and it was done quite well. Will be back to try other dishes.

I had some time before a drinks meeting and decided to grab dinner at NE Chinese. The Pork dish I enjoyed was excellent with fresh vegetables and grilled meat seasoned to perfection. The prices were reasonable for the size of the portions and the staff were very kind and hospitable.

name: Zhu Shi Fu Barbecue （朱师傅烧烤）
address: 2515 Summit St, Columbus, OH 43202, USA

reviews.text:
1 word. Yum! This place was insanely great. Drove all the way from Cle and still crave their oysters and skewers. Everything was freshly made. Prices were not bad for the portion and amount of food given. Service was fast and servers were great. Place was very clean and quiet. Plenty of tables too! Overall, had a fantastic visit. There’s no parking lot so basically you’ll have to find street parking.

Also- while eating, there were a handful of take out orders. So if you can’t stop by, make sure to order some take out!

The skewers were really tasty, my favorites were the beef and the chicken wings! The hot dog fried rice was also really good! Normally I don’t talk about other things outside of the food, but I have to give bonus points to the fancy interior design of the place, as it really felt like I was smack in an alley of a night market. My only complaint is that if you’re with a group, you have to order the food altogether. And so it can be a problem if someone orders way less food than the other, as the bill does not show who order what.

My wife and I recently had our third meal at Zhu Shi Fu Barbecue, and once again, it was excellent. The meat was incredibly fresh and flavorful, just like on our previous visits. The quality of the food and the friendly service continue to impress us. We look forward to dining here again soon!

This is a super nice restaurant with an authentic flavor! The skewers taste like the late-night street food I had in China. The staff is very friendly and thoughtful—they even offered us chair mats to provide more comfort. I will definitely come back and recommend it to friends!

We were very excited to try Zhu Shi Fu as soon as they had their soft opening! Parking was a little tricky and we had street parking. We came in at 5pm and the service was extremely slow. The server missed up our table number so by the time the group after us was served our food still didn’t come up. As apology, they brought us two appetizers before we waited for our first order (that wasn’t an appetizer) to come. The flavor of food was okay, we were disappointed to find out the special lamb skewer was not hot when it was served to us. And the burning candle under the device wasn’t strong enough to warm up the lamb, we had to remove the plate and grill the lamb on actual but tiny flame! Hope they improve their speed at serving diners!

address: 2361 N High St, Columbus, OH 43202, USA

reviews.text: We stopped here as Ruby Tuesdays was closed. Lucky us. My wife has lived in Tooting, London. This area specialises in Asian food. The meal was as good as anything produced there. The cook must have been Bangladeshi. We had  beef, chicken and vegetable dishes medium spicy. It tasted mild to medium to our palette. We took some home and the flavours were intensified the next day. Money well spent.

This Indian restaurant is authentic and fantastic. The location is close to the north campus. I came to their lunch buffet. The price was reasonable for students and there were a variety of great items. Their lamb curry was phenomenal, much better than chicken ones. Lamb tasted juicy and tender. Their tofu curry was also amazing. Their rice pudding and Indian milk tea tasted amazing as a dessert. The place was clean and service was excellent.

Update: After being to many Indian buffets afround columbus I feel that New Taj Mahal is not very creative and flavorful as others. For the same price there are many other better options.

This place serves a good Indian Lunch Buffet. I like this place as it has many options to try from. The food taste is good overall, can’t complain if some items do not taste very good. It is never very crowded and accessible. The flavors are okay. The service is also good. If you wanna try more Indian dishes in one time, go for their lunch buffet. My go to place for good Indian food!

My boyfriend and I came here and had a delightful meal. I got the paneer tikka masala and it was perfect! He got chicken vindaloo and liked it, though he got “hot” on the spice scale and thought it was quite spicy (rightfully  so). The rice and butter naan were delicious.

Definitely one of the best places to eat in town, especially if you like curry/Indian food.  I go often for the lunch buffet.  It is outstanding!  Several great options and everything was really good.  Great menu dishes too.  The place is a little old, but the food definitely makes up for it.

address: 3296 N High St, Columbus, OH 43202, USA

reviews.text: Wonderful food. We were visiting from out of town and went there 2 times! The diverse menu and the tasty execution of their dishes makes it worth more than one visit. I got the pad thai and it had a real depth of flavor I was not expecting. Most places it is very basic. Here is had sprouts, caramelized onions, and green onions. It was great. My husband goes for more american food and had a couple of different subs. They were very good. Also had the tuna bowl. Not very spicy but very good. All reasonably priced as well. Laid back atmosphere. Highly recommend.

We both got the general tso’s chicken, sauce was a bit gritty but it still had good flavor and the chicken was crispy. Would still get it again. This is a good place to stop in for lunch and they’ll get your food out quick.

Both the Thai and the American menu are solid and it's still a decent value. I like that the salad bar is staff-serviced but enclosed. You simply choose which ingredients you want and they'll even toss it for you in dressing of choice. We shared a salad and Philly and it was really a filling combo. The Thai food is where it's at though! Happy to visit this family owned small biz!
A very nice little cafe with lots of different foods to choose from. I can't wait to come back and try something else! This is a great place to go with friends.

This is my absolute vote food spot in not only Clintonville, but Columbus. An odd mix of deli/Asian fusion/salad bar/bagel sandwich/bubble tea shop! You can get a high quality lox bagel, or the best dragon roll you’ve ever had. The vibe is great for studying, or popping in for a quality casual lunch with family or friends.

I cannot recommend enough, and I cannot emphasize how much I mean that. For the last 10 years of my life Cornerstone has been a staple that has never disappointed.

Service and place was nice. Plenty of seating. They gave me paper menu since I don't really do the whole scanning menu thing. Service was quick and very courteous. Good work. I like to sit at the tree, which doesn't have a lot of room as far as maybe eating a pizza, but is my favorite spot

Brews:

Bought some to-go pumpkin sours!
Love, love, love! Beer is amazing, food is amazing, and service is always top notch. I’ve had a couple of mishaps and they were handled beautifully. Staff are down to earth and very knowledgeable
My husband and I went here last night for a quick date and it was delicious! Great beer and burgers and the bartender was super nice and attentive. Will be coming back whenever we're in Cville!

Stopped in tonight after the football game with a small group and was overly impressed with the quick & friendly service despite their busyness. Although I didn’t order a brew, the pizza & cheeseburger + fries were served super hot & so yummy! We will be back if we ever visit Columbus again!

I’ve always wanted a “neighborhood pub” where I know I’ll find good beer, good food, and good people. Derive checks off all three! There’s never a bad night to stop by, but if you don’t come for the Wednesday burger and draft deal, you are doing it wrong.

name: Layered Brew
address: 2864 N High St #1, Columbus, OH 43202, USA

reviews.text: The atmosphere is rather lack luster. The tables are sticky, filthy and ready to fall apart. The service was fine, when my friend and I rang the buzzer,(we hadn't a clue how this place operated as it was our first time in the building) the employee that came out was rather helpful and informative. However,  the coffee, the main staple, left a craters worth to wish for. It was like milk with a dash of flavor. Even the oat milk that was subbed in had no taste. 8 dollars is MUCH too pricey for suck lack luster quality. And my friend ordered an iced drink. Drink being used lightly as there were maybe a few sips with more than half of the 24 oz cup being filled with crushed ice. I truly wish I were exaggerating here. And the tax for the drinks was rather strange too. I truly wish ny experience had been better, but I even warned some friends that were curious about this place to not come here.

Virginia with Offline - The blonde lady that helped me was so nice and patient! She answered questions and was quick and overall just a great experience! I got the refresher with lemonade; my only feedback on the drink is maybe offer a carbonated version!! otherwise, delicious!!! I also got the avocado toast. It was good, but I felt like it needed something to really make it pop. The olive oil was a fantastic touch, but maybe add some balsamic vinegar, maybe a little dill or even a honey packet to spice up the flavor! Overall fantastic service, decent food and quick.
So yummy!! Love all the vegan/vegetarian options. Easy and convenient pickup.

Have seen this place and thought about trying it before and finally decided to go with my friend because they wanted a lavender latte and remembered them having that as an option here. When we got there found out you had to order online and were a bit taken back on the prices for the coffee but decided to go ahead and get it anyways since we were already there. I ordered a 24 oz iced pistachio latte also was charged .56 tax and debated not getting it because the price for it was $8 but friend ordered already so I decided to and wish I hadn’t wasted my money. My latte had only a faint hint of pistachio to it and mainly just tasted like milk wish a splash of coffee. Also had my cup almost compelled with ice as well. I usually get iced coffee and was shocked by the amount of ice they had in theirs was over 3/4ths of my cup filled after the coffee was finished
Best damn coffee you can get in Columbus. Great staff and even better product. Worth every penny. I have never bought something here that I didn’t love.

address: 355 E Hudson St, Columbus, OH 43202, USA

reviews.text:
The food is always so fresh and tasty, and it is at a good price too. Also, they are also open late.
Just make sure you bring cash since it's cash only
Also this place is very authentic and they offer a range of options on their menu.
I drive Uber and just stopped by here to get a taco. I got it for $3 in 3 minutes and it was provided with fresh cilantro radish cucumber with a nice salsa and the corn tortilla was also fresh.
but I've been here many times and it's always good. The baleda are nice also.

Late night dining that hit the spot 🙌
Big variety of food options with the comida here!! Friendly staff members & Real Hispanics making the grub too....🤠
Decently priced food for size and quality of food's.
Tasty Burrito & Taco's plus more here....
FYI....Cash 🤑 Only joint⚠️

I got the shrimp quesadilla, shrimp empanada and chicken tamale and they’re all amazing!!! So flavorful unlike most other Mexican spots. I’m glad they’re open so late too it’s hard to find good food when I’m working late. Will be coming again!!
Got three pork tacos for $9; they were very tasty and worth the price! Definitely recommend! 👌🏾

This was my first time eating here, so I ordered several menu items. I ordered the #3 Bandeja Paisa, carnitas nachos, empanadas, tamales, Shrimp taco Supreme and chorizo taco supreme. The Carnitas nachos was by far the best of everything that I ordered, which is alarming because it literally causes for the least amount of skill or time to be put into it. Next, we have the empanadas which were stuffed with an appropriate amount of filling and fried perfectly, however someone forgot to put the salt in the empanada pastry and the filling which was bland as can be and was not satisfying even in the least. Next, we have the tamales which was prepared with way too much masa to filling ratio. I felt like I was just eating nothing but overly dense steamed masa and much like the empanadas had zero flavor to it whatsoever. And lastly, the shrimp and chorizo taco supreme. Fire starters, I got two chorizo taco Supremes instead of one shrimp and one chorizo so, there’s an issue right there of attention to detail. Along with that there was nothing spectacular about this taco. I mean, the presentation was misleading because it looked like a great taco but when I ate it, the chorizo was dry. It was not a good quality chorizo whatsoever. Just tasted like I was eating finely ground sausage with none of the spice mix that you expect in chorizo very disappointing. A piece of advice to this food truck, salt is not the enemy of great food. Furthermore, don’t put items on your menu that you do not have a qualified cook to prepare. It’s disappointing to your customers.

name: Hudson 29 Kitchen + Drink
address: 1600 W Lane Ave, Upper Arlington, OH 43221, USA

reviews.text:
Great ambience at this location in particular.  Food is always fantastic as well as service. We love all the booths around their bar here, it's very cozy. We had the short rib hash on the brunch menu and the corn and avocado side instead of potatoes. Hubs had the tenderloin with campari tomatoes and feta, which is delicious! Their coffee is best in the city in my opinion!

Great service and greeted and seated right away. They always have a daily omelet for weekend brunch. Great spot, it's always perfect!

We stopped at Hudson 29 around 3:00 in the afternoon. My wife had blackened fish sandwich which came with fries and she absolutely loved it. I got Rigatoni Bolognese and I suspect that it was wonderful but I discovered it would not be one of my favorite dishes. That was probably me. The atmosphere was good and in the time slot it was quiet. The surprise was that I found the service average. I think she was probably new. Overall it was a great place and I would go back.

I'm from out of state and a friend who is a native recommended meeting here for a late lunch. What a great choice! The atmosphere was almost like a "lounge" -- dark and quiet. We shared a couple of appetizers, and I crushed a plate of sushi and the corn and avocado side. Everything was on point, and our server was fantastic.

One of my best meals of 2024.  It was outstanding from start to finish. The seabass was recommended and it was amazing.  Cooked perfectly and with an amazing sauce. Served over rice. Others in my party enjoyed their meals as well.  We started with the chicked meatballs - also great. I appreciated the selection of draft beers and wine by the glass.  Outstanding place!

We came here to celebrate my son's sixteenth birthday & Hudson 29 DID NOT disappoint! The food was excellent, the atmosphere was beautiful, & the service was top-tier! I definitely would love to come back here!

name: Ajs tacos
address: 2864 N High St, Columbus, OH 43202, USA

reviews.text:
Insanely Good Tacos.
I ordered the street tacos with beef/chicken and cheese.
Honestly, I’ve never had tacos this good before. The way the shells are cooked perfectly And they have a perfect amount of cheese. The meats dipped in the green sauce are very good. The beef is seasoned really well.
When you put that all together, you have amazing tacos!  I will definitely be back for more tacos and excited to try new things like their burrito and cheese chicken quesadilla.
Very nice staff as well, very polite.

Delicious authentic tacos dipped in consume with sides of sauce as well to add to the deliciousness! 🌮 I love how friendly and kind the staff are anx so helpful. Overall, loved it. I also love the added 2 cucumbers larger slices of cucumbers to the street tacos. 🥒 My favorite out of the street tacos was the chicken one and my absolute favorite thing is the #1 combo 3 tacos with consume. 😍 Thanks again! ♥️♥️ Will be back 💃🏽
I order from here probably weekly and it’s consistently some of the best. I always get the birria and shrimp tacos. Both phenomenal and still hot upon delivery.

Came due to great reviews placed an order waited 50 minutes before receiving it. We asked after it got to the 20 min mark they said it would be right out which was a lie because it took another half an hour. Clearly the food had been sitting for a while my cheese Quesadilla was room temperature on the verge of cool tasted like cardboard. My boyfriends steak on his tostada was cold. I wish places would turn off door dash orders if they don't have the staff to handle it, It truly makes in person experiences suffer. We won't be back.

BEST IN TOWN. Phenomenal nachos! That's my favorite menu item but honestly everything is good.

The birria is incredible. The consomé is unmatched. They make their nacho chips fresh and also have incredible toastadas, taquitos, and ramen.

The owners are so nice and service is quick. This is one of my favorite places to eat! Definitely check it out!

reviews.text: The food here is amazing, being from NY this is as close to halal as I’ll find. Portions were generous and cooked well. If you’re looking for a good burger this place has it too. Will definitely come back again! The owner cares a lot about his customers and does it all right-

I found my new favorite place!!! The prices are bomb, the food is bomb and the people who work here are whatever word is better than bomb I’ve been looking for a place like this since I moved home from Georgia the wings, the fries everything y’all need to tap in!!!!

We came all the way from South Florida & found this great place! I got the smash burger and tres leches & it honestly was amazing. It satisfied my appetite. I’m very picky and choosey when it comes to smash burgers so I really must say that this one went above and beyond my expectations. The tres leches was moist and soooo smooth. It was really delicious. I was grateful to have an encounter with the owner and he was very kind and welcoming. If I’m ever in Columbus Ohio again, I will definitely come here for a round 2.

The food is always amazing, the customer service is very kind and even the customers are nice, area is always clean even if i come right before close and they always treat us with so much respect, food also is very quick and is always very fresh, highly recommend

Apparently it's a take out only place. So we ordered our food, when I got the notification for the food being ready, we rang the doorbell, then they said our food was almost done, still waited at least an additional 10 minutes. We took the food home, the fries were ok, but the burgers were super dry despite being drowned in sauce, that we couldn't finish it(they overcooked both the bun and burger) but the gyro was ok at least. Not coming back... There was also no parking, so we parked across the street.

name: Katalina's, Too!
address: 3481 N High St, Columbus, OH 43214, USA

reviews.text:
Really enjoyed my breakfast here.  I got the pancake balls with Nutella and veggie sausage patties AND the Big Ol' Burrito (I had a to go box) both were very good!  I really like the atmosphere.  Parking fills up quickly but there are side streets where you can find a spot.  It was a little more expensive than I had planned, but that won't keep me from going back-AND I got two meals sooo...
I highly recommend this place if you're tired of the same old breakfast fare and atmosphere!

Hard to recommend friends come try this with their pricing vs. the overly complex breakfast dishes. 2x kids French toast + the avocado toast w/ scrambled eggs + the chicken egg sandwich + order of pancake balls + drinks = $106.
This place is SO delicious it will not disappoint. The breakfast tacos are worth the hype and the big ol burrito was too. The pancakes balls filled with pumpkin apple butter were delicious!

Good breakfast place. Tried the Dulce de leche pancake balls. Good, not too sweet. Sweet and spicy bacon had good flavor  but a bit limp. Chicken breakfast sandwich also good. Potatoes very soggy. $36 for 2 meals.
No parking. Street parking only.

Came to this place because it was highly rated and located near our Airbnb in Columbus. Found the restaurant easily enough and there was parking directly behind the restaurant that could be accessed from the alley.

The menu had so many great choices! We settled on the eggs in the basket with over easy eggs and the breakfast tacos.

Food came quickly, and was hot and fresh. We enjoyed both entrees accompanied by the peaches and scream salsa!

As for the food, the elote corn was so tasty! The potatoes were very flavorful, and the breakfast tacos were a hit with both of us!

This salsa is not locally produced as it's produced in Denver Colorado.

The service was friendly and attentive as well as helpful with the menu.

We love all the quotes on the walls and the interior décor.

reviews.text: The best Cane’s that I have been. This location is close to the Ohio state sport center. Their dining room is full of Buckeye elements. Their chicken fingers are always fresh and juicy with their signature sauce. Service is fast and helpful.

Tried for the first time. Chicken has a good flavor. Food is 4/5. I am giving 2/5 because they make you buy the sauce for Chicken tenders and the one serving you buy is not enough for the food you get. . On top,  They only offer ketchup. No other condiments. Food is great please don't make customers buy the sauce. It should be complementary.

I’ve never been to this chain and really enjoy a change in the “traditional chicken, fries and coleslaw”.
Sauce and Texas toast was a refreshing change with the lemonade 🍋.
Hot food, prompt and friendly service and the restaurant was spotless.
Great spot for a meal!

Delicious. Plain delicious. Love their sauce, but the chicken itself is hands down perfect. The side dishes are yummy too, and the menu is small enough that you don’t have to make a wrong choice. It’s all good!
The staff at this location were so friendly, and the decor was great. Highly recommend.

Everything was perfect! That's really all there is to say. Really good pieces of chicken piping hot and crispy, fries still good after 10 minutes getting it home. I would not change a thing about that order.

reviews.text: Fried rice was basically white rice with a little bit of egg in it. The General Tso’s was alright, but not really flavorful. My coworker ordered the orange chicken and it was so gross and mushy looking. She tried a bite and threw the rest out. Ordered egg rolls and one only got one roll. Definitely wouldn’t recommend.

I ordered Fried Rice and fried rice noodles. Generally speaking, it was a good dining experience. They are all cooked with fresh ingredients and spices, and the taste is also great, making people feel very satisfied. The environment of the restaurant is also very good, clean and tidy.
I always have a good experience dining here or ordering take out. The staff are also very friendly. Food is equally as on point. Pictured is their delicious fish and eggplant claypot.
Food was great! Warm and delicious even when it was super busy. The only down side was it took a while for someone to recognize I needed assistance

Automatic gratuity for a party of 2 for mediocre service and ok food. The auto gratuity is 30% that they applied onto my bill without asking or having is posted anywhere. Is that just how they treat minority customers they assume won’t tip? Or just the usual? The orange chicken was good, Crab Rangoon was good but my half duck was luke warm and lacked flavor. Both white rice and brown rice were DIGUSTING. We came 2 hours before close and there was only 1 other table that was leaving and only 1 other table that came in while we were there; plus less than a handful of to go or Uber orders during our visit. The point is; they could have made our food ATLEAST hot. Woke up today browsing my bank statements and they also included an additional charge so my bill that was originally 67 ended up being 82 dollars altogether?? I’m not going to dispute it or call there because I’ve noticed some foreign owned franchises have some very shady practices but I Will obviously never return. Just a heads up to someone who may be attracted to this scummy place by the initial nice decor of the restaurant.

address: 590 Oakland Park Ave, Columbus, OH 43214, USA

reviews.text: Italian sub!!!!!  I was torn between oak burger and Italian sub and asked bartender.  Him along with 2 random people next to me all said it at same time.  It was a great sub, but make sure you are hungry, it's big.  Loved the atmosphere and service too.
They make a killer Italian sub that keeps me coming back and they do fun stuff too like trivia I had a fun time it turns out me and my mom make a good team we got second place :)

I was curious since I had heard so much about the Italian sub there. So I want to try it, and they were right! It’s a nice toasted sub, good size, and reasonable price. It has a “bar” atmosphere, which I don’t mind. I’ll certainly go back when I’m in the area.

If you want a true neighborhood pub with a laid-back set of regulars and a great hot Italian sub for 10 bucks, just go.  Good stuff on tap, and anything else is close at hand.  Forget paying a month's wages for a good meal and a cool place.  India Oak is nothing fancy, but everything is truly good!  Enjoy an easy time.

Have been meaning to go to this place (Indian Oak Grill) forever and always found a reason not to go. Well finally decided to go. After sitting down I was greeted by Nick the bartender. Decided to order the Chili and the Italian Sub. The chili had a nice blend of beans, hamburger, tomatoes, onions, peppers and spices. It had just a slight kick to it which was just right. No wonder why it is listed as one of the best in town. On to the sub sandwich. It has hard salami, hot ham, provolone cheese, lettuce, onion, tomatoes, banana peppers and Italian dressing on I believe an Auddino's bun that seemed to been pressed by a Panini Press to heat it up and to melt the cheese. It made for a phenomenal sandwich. Nick checked on me numerous times and refilled my drink. Well everything I read about this place was true. Their food is off the chart. Check them out.
